text: it’s october, my favorite month! lots of fun personal highlights, fall weather, halloween, etc. it’s also domestic violence awareness month, a time of year that is super important to me and lots of people i know. like one in four women, i’ve experienced domestic violence. i used to (and still often am) super ashamed of this, but it’s getting easier now that so many people are sharing their stories with #metoo. i still don’t share the details very often, because i don’t like to be vulnerable and don’t want to be a downer, but i’m at least comfortable talking a little bit about it now. like right at this very moment! 💜 anyway, in honor of survivors this month, @miltonandmargies is donating 10% of all sales to @rundvoutoftown! (i’m also doing a fundraiser personally, so let me know if you want to donate that way.) @rundvoutoftown is a collective of 10 domestic violence service providers throughout chicago working together to end domestic violence. they work to bring awareness to dv, provide preventive work, and offer support to survivors and their families. i love this organization, and hope you’ll buy a candle this month to help support them! 💜💜💜 if you feel comfortable sharing anything about your own experiences, use #survivorspeaks (📷 by @pipercarter)

text: with all the ugliness out there currently being lobbed towards women and especially towards women of color, i was especially moved by the chalkboard art that jasper’s 4th grade teacher made to coincide with michaelmas. he shared with us parents his inspiration behind his idea of turning st. michael into michaela- “my hope is that this picture can live and grow in the children:  a female michaela, woman of color, striding forth as the heroic dragon conqueror.  i made a drawing of her suppressing the dragon...”💛🐉✨ we need more men and teachers like this: who create and hold that vision for the children of women as conquerors and role models; to share stories of bad ass epic women who are legit slaying dragons. then these girls will know they can and these boys will see women who rule as the norm. his drawing means so much to me. as any of you know if you scroll back a few, i had a hard week this week as so many other women did. i encouraged him to make a print or card of this work bc i will frame it. #slayingdragons #waldorfeducation #fourthgradeteacher #waldorfchalkboard #michaelmas  #timesup #metoo #stopkavanaugh #jasdevendra

text: saffron didn't report her sexual assault for 28 years. she was raped in the late 1980s, when she was 17, and was so terrified the police wouldn't believe her that she stayed silent. "having been through such a traumatic experience, the idea of speaking about it and not being believed was too much," she says. "people who are raped blame themselves, so the idea of speaking out is terrifying. that is one of the most terrifying things: the shame." saffron's story captures the difficulty that survivors of rape and sexual assault face when sharing their stories - and why so many people stay silent. the problem is the focus of raped: my story, a channel 5 documentary that airs tonight. in the wake of the revelations around harvey weinstein and the #metoo campaign, it aims to shine a light on how survivors internalise what has happened to them and become paralysed by fear.

text:
#reapthewhirlwind #deargirl #history won't silence #herstory ™  #globalfratparty™ is over  #cleanupisabitch 
respectwomenstillgirls🌸
#internationaldayofthegirl
#dayofthegirl " in hard times" daysofeve☯️™ © clili™ #comingoutday #comingout "if she can make it thru this mess, then maybe so can i - in hard times ... we could be listening -" women #blacklivesmatter lgbt rights #climatechange #cleanwater cleanair #metoo #noh8  roe marchforourlives 
homies :  voteforourlives 👊🏾👊🏼👊🏽☑️ a therapist once shared this truestory + analogy w me . 
she'd had a "client" who was a child victim of #childabuse - he was brought 2 her office covered in bruises. when she asked him - "did he know why he was in her office .." his response : "because i was a bad boy?" therapist explained 2 me that the nature of abuse + intention of abuser is 2 blame the victim victim-shaming : manipulates victim in2 blaming themselves + divided from emotional intelligence 
thus abuser "gets away" w it by manipulating victim in completion of intention - victim harms themselves while "keeping secrets " on behalf of abuser - due 2 fear or misplaced loyalty  ie. abused kids r still loyal 2 parents ; others want to be loyal 2 friends ... all is fueled by shame ;

she related this story 2 me bc when i told her the story of my childhood -
 she said i reminded her of that little boy shouldering the task of staying loyal 2 an abusive family ;  i had 2 learn 2 sayno to abusive people + neveragain blame myself ; 
otherwise i'd go thru life allowing others to behave this way, and take it upon myself to defend them ... never realizing they were harming me .... i relate this story 4 those who see themselves in it. 
for those who need it's wisdom ;
 it has served me well + i encourage victims of abuse 2 reject #victimshaming wherever it is found.

it doesn't have to be a severe form of abuse...it could be an unkindness that stays with you for days - undermining your confidence or your sense of how the world might turn out for you ... you see the unkind person is miserable ...and all they know - is to pass it on ... but i say : pass this on :  together 
we can build a kinder world 
end pathology
#billboardpride

text:
christine blasey lived in potomac, maryland in 1985.

christine was arrested in a traffic stop and ticketd on june 14, 1985 (friday) in catawba county north carlina.

she was charged with a traffic misdemeanor – no big deal.  it was disposed on sept 11, 1985.

but there’s more.
there were two other cases on june 17, 1985 (monday). they were also in catawba county on a different day and are under case type – criminal.  this might be the same case, but two different records were given. 
the interesting thing about these two cases against christine blasey ford is that they were last updated on july 7, 2018.

in her testimony ford said she contacted the washington post tip line (and democrat lawmakers) on july 6th.
that is why july 7th, 2018 is so coincidental.

is that when they were expunged?

ford’s letter to rep. eschoo and senator feinstein was dated on july 30, 2018 and signed by christine blasey.
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - 
#confirmkavanaugh #brettkavanaugh #istandwithkavanaugh #wwg1wga #walkaway #lovewins #maga #metoo

text:
i just saw connie chung's story of her family doctor. when i was working in an emergency department, i was trying to admit a patient.. the admitting doctor kept trying to humiliate me into sending the patient home - and began to say a lot of lewd and aggressive things when i wasn't going with his plan. if you are a dad with a daughter, you would have punched him if you'd heard it. i knew i could create a fuss but it would be his word against mine etc. different day, same story. 
i was scared to report him. i had kids and thought he might come after me. the next day the hospital administration called and asked me to make a formal report about it. it turns out the  wonderful er nurses reported him on my behalf! i explained about the fear for my family’s safety. 
the administrator then went off record: two patients had accused him of raping them in a closed exam room with no supervision (that in of itself is weird - even i always have a chaperone) but they were deemed "women with issues" and it was his word against theirs. i immediately made a formal report and he eventually lost his license and was also found to be abusing alcohol and drugs. but i almost let it go. how many more patients would he have raped? sexual violence is ubiquitous and it’s time people understood this. i have so many friends who have been molested, raped, etc. and most never reported. 
for what it's worth, this is not a commentary on kavnanaugh, or his innocence, guilt or even politics. i stand with all of my many friends who have been raped, molested, harassed, not believed, victimized. if the scope seems unbelievable to you, you are lucky. so lucky - you have no idea. count your blessings but believe the victims. 
to wrap this up, i'd like to just state from the bottom of my heart: as a mother to a son and daughter, i'd much rather risk the very small chance of a false allegation to my son than keeping the status quo of sexual violence for my daughter. look at the statistics of false allegations versus rape; to use an emergency medicine analogy, it's like forgoing one's seatbelt because it might trap you in the car and kill you. edited to fit 2200 characterfull story on fb. #acep2018

text_retweet:
listen up ladies ❤️ #repost @glennondoyle with @get_repost
・・・
are you ready to turn your rage into change?

many of you have been waiting for me to share what’s next for us as women, as warriors, as citizens. you have no idea how seriously i take that trust and responsibility. 
it’s not easy for me to ask anything of you. your lives are hard and exhausting and filled to the brim already.  my job, my mission for the past thirteen years has been to serve you.

in this moment in history, the purest way i can continue to serve you is to ask something of you. to invite you to rise up and unite your voices, bodies, power and say:
enough.
enough systematic and celebrated racism. 
enough ignoring and laughing at survivors’ pain. 
enough terrified migrant children transported to middle of the desert, in the middle of the night. 
enough institutionally enforced wealth for the richest americans while so many americans toil in intergenerational poverty. 
enough.

i believe that this, this is the moment in which we each make a decision:
we go either back to sleep or stay wide awake.
we either give up or give hell. 
we either lay down and surrender or rise up and fight for each other.
we either turn our rage into change, or we let it eat us alive. 
we’re going to turn our rage into change. for us, and for our children. for everyone’s children. so that one day, when my daughters and son ask how i reacted during these dangerous times, i’ll be able to say: like this. i’ll be able to point to pictures and tell them stories about the power of sisterhood. i’ll be able to say: right here, babies. this is how your mama showed up for you. and for her sisters. and for herself.

a group of fierce and brilliant women activists (led by women of color) and i have been plotting tirelessly all week. we have a plan. 
this is how we are going to show up:
every friday from this friday, oct 5, through nov 23, we are going to turn our rage into change through #blackfridays

come back tomorrow for friday’s action items!  for tonight: tag every good human you know, share share & let’s let the world know it’s revolution eve eve!!!! love fury and relentless hope,
g
#blackfridays #timesup #metoo

text:
in honor of #meangirlsday... #youcantsitwithus ✋🏻 #wednesday #october3rd .
.
i never was one of those girls in hs. i did run with the “cool crowd”, or as my parents put it, “the fast crowd” 😂, but i was always involved in a lot of different extra curricular activities so i had lots of different friends in different groups, clubs, cliques, age ranges... and i absolutely loved that. to this day, i have all different kinds of friends in different walks of life and i always enjoy meeting and making new ones 🤗 .
.
in hs, my heart always broke when i saw someone sitting alone 💔 probably because in eighth grade, my parents made me move. i decided that i was going to “punish them” by not making any friends at my new school. (not my smartest decision ever... 🙄) on the first few days of school i stuck to my guns and by the end of the week, the entire grade knew me as “the mute”. i ended up making friends with some very lovely girls, but the nickname had already stuck, especially with the guys, and that’s how everyone knew me and called out to me in the hallways, for the rest of the year. to this day, my heart wells up with tears every time i hear a bullying story 😢
.
on the positive, i absolutely love this movie. i fell in love with rachel mcadams and her talent, was in awe of how brilliantly @mingey could play dumb 🤓 and began routing for @lindsaylohan again ❤️ it actually really helped with bringing about a ground-breaking shift in the female culture by bringing awareness to just how mean girls can be to each other. (some argue, even more so than men... i would actually have to agree with that 🤷🏼‍♀️) .
.
in my past acting work, i’ve often been cast as one of those mean, popular girls, which i attribute to knowing how women can be, and tapping into my own past and recent encounters. but, i’m pleased to see a big shift taking place. especially on social media. there’s obviously been a lot of changes over the past year and no matter what your beliefs are, you’ll have to agree that it’s nice to see women bonding and supporting one another on here ❤️ right @jen_baute?😘
.
so thank you tina fey for causing a stir 14 years ago! art really does have an impact 😌🎭
name: Caroline Heinle
tweet_full:
in honor of #meangirlsday... #youcan notsitwithus ✋🏻 #wednesday #october3rd .
.
i never was one of those girls in hs. i did run with the “cool crowd”, or as my parents put it, “the fast crowd” 😂, but i was always involved in a lot of different extra curricular activities so i had lots of different friends in different groups, clubs, cliques, age ranges... and i absolutely loved that. to this day, i have all different kinds of friends in different walks of life and i always enjoy meeting and making new ones 🤗 .
.
in hs, my heart always broke when i saw someone sitting alone 💔 probably because in eighth grade, my parents made me move. i decided that i was going to “punish them” by not making any friends at my new school. (not my smartest decision ever... 🙄) on the first few days of school i stuck to my guns and by the end of the week, the entire grade knew me as “the mute”. i ended up making friends with some very lovely girls, but the nickname had already stuck, especially with the guys, and that’s how everyone knew me and called out to me in the hallways, for the rest of the year. to this day, my heart wells up with tears every time i hear a bullying story 😢
.
on the positive, i absolutely love this movie. i fell in love with rachel mcadams and her talent, was in awe of how brilliantly @mingey could play dumb 🤓 and began routing for @lindsaylohan again ❤️ it actually really helped with bringing about a ground-breaking shift in the female culture by bringing awareness to just how mean girls can be to each other. (some argue, even more so than men... i would actually have to agree with that 🤷🏼‍♀️) .

i believe you

text:
james roche is my sister’s brother in law and we were in the same wedding party when my sister got married. i don’t know him very well like my sister,
of course, but it just so happens that he was brett kavanaugh’s roommate at yale. quite surreal seeing him on tv as he looks and reminds me very much like his sibling, my own brother in law.  people, this is a bfd and quite rare, it’s not often to see a man willing to risk his reputation, personal, family and business life by publicly speaking his truth on such a controversial and also political issue on a widespread and national level. for that, we have ronan farrow, a record breaking journalist for the #metoo movement, to thank for james coming forward. if not for ronan’s aggressive and relentless journalistic approach and push for encouragement, james would never have put the spotlight on himself that he neither wanted nor asked for but with ronan’s persistence, he decided not to hide behind the truth.  with everything to lose and little to nothing to gain, it takes great admirable courage for him to say,
hey, this guy, under oath for a lifetime supreme court position, lied for sure about certain things in the hearing. not only was james brett’s roommate, he also knew debbie ramirez on a more personal level as he was friends and more social with her at yale. although he is not a witness to any of brett’s sexual activity that debbie’s accusing of, he believes there is zero chance that she is making her story up. whether the sexual assault/misconduct allegations are true or not, kavanaugh lied under oath at one point and another about his youth, period.  and what’s worrying is that small lies can also be much bigger lies for someone who could sit in the supreme court. “what struck me and made me more interested in speaking out ... is not only did i know that he wasn't telling the truth," roche said. "i knew that he knew that he wasn't telling the truth." james, thank you. #ibelieveher and #ibelievetheroommate #stopkavanaugh #kavanope either #withdraw or #votenokavanaugh

text:
content warning (mental health, assault, kavanaugh)
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
person at the bus stop: are you on your way to the stop kavanaugh rally?

me: no.

person stares.

me: it's honestly too triggering for me.

person: yeah, it's hard for a lot of people. you should still go though.
.
.
.
i've been having a very tough time. and it feels selfish. it's everywhere - on social media, at the bus stop, at work on the cover of the paper, at work in people's mouths, in memories i don't think i'll ever lose. i'm trying to not to think about it, talk about it. but i also want to know what's going on. i also want to pull out my hair and pummel every smug looking man i see.
.
i don't know. survivor doesn't feel like the right word. i know that there are parts of me that did not survive.
.
but here's to honesty about how i'm doing and dyeing my hair with some old overtone conditioner i had instead of pulling it out in handfuls.
.
#metoo

⚠️ #religion ⚠️ zeinab sekaanvand, 24, was 15 when she married her husband and was jailed at age 17 for stabbing him to death after a confession that she later retracted. she said she had been #tortured and interrogated with no lawyer present.

she said she had been #abused by her husband and #raped several times by her brother-in-law, who told her that if she accepted responsibility, he could pardon her, which is accepted under #islamic law.

despite retracting her statement, the judge refused to order another inquiry, and she was sentenced to death. she was #executed on tuesday morning in uremieh central prison, west azerbaijan province. #think #metoo #humanity #nogod #noreligion #intelligence #kindness #logic ❤️ #compassion

text:
i’ve stayed silent the last few weeks not because i don’t care, but because if i opened my mouth, i only had anger come out. i don’t want that. but watching what has unfolded the past few weeks with the fiasco that is brett kavanaugh has left me with a knot in my throat. 
it was only 6 months ago that racheal stirling and i decided to come forward publicly for the first time about what happened to us when we reported our sexual assaults to the nypd. what is not mentioned is that, when i first came forward anonymously on social media, the amount of hatred, animosity i received from mostly men on the internet. slut, whore, “she’s deserved it,” “bitch got what she asked for” were some of the benign messages i got. 
watching what has unfolded with christine’s coming forward is exactly what racheal and i have been fighting for. but what it feels like is that our stories made no difference. this country is still a patriarchy built on privilege, and the amount of tears, fear and fight we and others have put into making a difference has gotten us nowhere. 
it’s not only disheartening but terrifying to see the malignant patriarchy in its truest form in the highest places of our government. it’s fucking terrifying.

so, i’m mad. i’m angry. i’m scared. but i do have hope. 
when dave and i first met at work, i kept my distance because he was exactly the type of man i feared. military born and bred and raised, years in the navy. i had never had a good run in with someone like that. i was wrong, however his mentality is the mentality of most well meaning privileged men — “let’s teach you self defense and that will protect you.”
he said that to me one night and i get angry and went off. he was shocked and didn’t understand, but wanted to. he said, “i am ignorant. please teach me.” i explained what racheal and i had done. what women have to fight against. when women who are sexually assaulted have to fight against. he had no idea. as a white privileged male, he had no idea. and then he said to me, “as a protected white male — what can i do to help?”
(continued in comments)
 @rachealstirling
name: IzzyRN
tweet_full:
i’ve stayed silent the last few weeks not because i don’t care, but because if i opened my mouth, i only had anger come out. i don’t want that. but watching what has unfolded the past few weeks with the fiasco that is brett kavanaugh has left me with a knot in my throat. 
it was only 6 months ago that racheal stirling and i decided to come forward publicly for the first time about what happened to us when we reported our sexual assaults to the nypd. what is not mentioned is that, when i first came forward anonymously on social media, the amount of hatred, animosity i received from mostly men on the internet. slut, whore, “she’s deserved it,” “bitch got what she asked for” were some of the benign messages i got. 
watching what has unfolded with christine’s coming forward is exactly what racheal and i have been fighting for. but what it feels like is that our stories made no difference. this country is still a patriarchy built on privilege, and the amount of tears, fear and fight we and others have put into making a difference has gotten us nowhere. 
it’s not only disheartening but terrifying to see the maligt patriarchy in its truest form in the highest places of our government. it’s fucking terrifying.

so, i’m mad. i’m angry. i’m scared. but i do have hope. 
when dave and i first met at work, i kept my distance because he was exactly the type of man i feared. military born and bred and raised, years in the navy. i had never had a good run in with someone like that. i was wrong, however his mentality is the mentality of most well meaning privileged men — “let’s teach you self defense and that will protect you.”
he said that to me one night and i get angry and went off. he was shocked and didn’t understand, but wanted to. he said, “i am ignorant. please teach me.” i explained what racheal and i had done. what women have to fight against. when women who are sexually assaulted have to fight against. he had no idea. as a white privileged male, he had no idea. and then he said to me, “as a protected white male — what can i do to help?”
(continued in comments)
 @rachealstirling

s e c o n d  a n n u a l // soda pop with a cop 🥤🚓 #advocate #idaho ——————————————————————
hi everyone, it's time for our second annual soda pop with a cop!
soda pop with a cop is happening october 4th & 5th. some of our local police officers will be there from 2-6 pm both days, so come on by!
when you purchase a purple soda and a purple sugar cookie, fizz bizz will donate $1/order to the family crisis center in honor of domestic violence awareness month. 
we love this event and are grateful to fizz bizz and rigby and jefferson county law enforcement for putting this together to raise awareness of domestic violence and stand with survivors. we look forward to seeing you there! 💜 —————————————————————— #lifestyle #family #loveshouldnthurt #october #enddv #byui #dvfacts #entrepreneur #fall #design #wellness #marketing #friends #idaho #timesup #metoo #health #breakthesilence #idaho #graphicdesign #treatyourself #dessert

text_retweet:
#repost @gracieandrachel with @get_repost
・・・
her
———
on the morning of thursday, september 27th, 2018, an eager anticipation woke us up in our brooklyn loft unusually early. with our hearts racing, we tuned into the hearings of dr. christine blasey ford and judge brett kavanaugh.
———
amidst dr. ford’s emotionally brave testimony, kavanaugh’s flippant denial, and an amalgamation of statements from an assembly of both incredibly compassionate and unbelievably ruthless senators, we made a new song. and it was for her.
———
once the hearings were over, we began putting a video together to more fully capture the inspiration behind this song. we wanted to point to women, from a range of walks of life, women who have taken a stance when it wasn’t necessarily easy to do so. our goal was to highlight the courage it takes to call something out loud and to stand up tall when the odds may not be in our favor.
———
the women in this piece are just a few among many who inspire us to continue to use our voices and demand to be heard. the conclusory chorus lyric “never look back again” doesn’t imply we shouldn’t look back on the women who have taught us how to lead the way — we most absolutely should — but that we should always move bravely into the future. we hope with our song to thank the women who have empowered us so selflessly and perhaps to inspire those still searching to find their strengths.
———
see the full video for “her” now! link in bio.
———
music and lyrics by gracie and rachel @gracieandrachel 
co-written and co-produced by garrett eaton @the_name_is_dame
mixed by steve wall @swallja 
video by gracie coates @graciecoates
———

text: these two pictures may look like they have nothing in common but they mean everything to me. the first picture was taken a year ago today, a few hours before i was assaulted in the school cafeteria. this picture was taken when another person was in the bathroom with me because i wasn’t safe walking down the school hallways by myself. for months i was terrified to go to school, i was scared to walk to the bathroom by myself, or walk to swim practice because i didn’t know if i would be chased down the hallway again, like it had happened many times before. i reported multiple times being harassed online and other stalking incidents and every time i was assured that i was safe...but i was told i just shouldn’t be alone in the hallway, if i could help it. a few days after being assured that i was safe was when the assault happened while i was waiting to go to a swim meet. this lead to a number of court visits, police escorts too and from school, and an impending anxiousness that began to consume me. for a month straight i refused to drive myself anywhere and i was in a constant state of fear. but through all of this i had an incredible support system. my friends, family, teachers, and coaches. my faith grew tremendously through this experience and i learned that everything rides on hope. i’ve learned that letting it out and letting go is incredibly hard but extremely worth it. and i’ve learned how liberating forgiveness really feels. this second picture is a lot happier, it was taken on the last day i had to set foot in a court room. the same day that my voice was finally heard and proper repercussions were given. it was also the day that i was finally able to let go of what had happened and focused on moving forward step by step (with my momma bear by my side as usual). i am not a victim to my circumstance, i am a survivor lead in hope, courage, and forgiveness who is breaking the silence💜#breakthesilence #metoo

text: october is national domestic violence awareness month.  every 9 seconds, a woman in the us is beaten, or assaulted by a current or ex significant other.  the us doj estimates 1.3 million women and 835k men are victims of physical violence by a partner every year.  this is me 4 yrs ago when my then boyfriend grabbed my arm, slammed my head into a concrete pillar, causing a concussion, repeatedly kicking me while not allowing me to have my phone to call the police in front of his teenage children.  he had never been physically abusive like this in the past but all the signs were there, i just didn’t want to see, i somehow thought he would never do something like this because he claimed to love me, said i was different, he said his ex’s didn’t understand him, they were crazy, ect.... the signs of escalating domestic abuse are clear, don’t be fooled into their magical thinking, your gut doesn’t lie, trust it, stay safe.  #domesticviolenceawareness #metoo #risingstrong #stigmafighter #endthestigma #stepup #tonyrobbinsupw #tonyrobbins #ishallnotbemoved #warrior #warriors #bravingthewilderness #firewalker

text_retweet:
#repost @trinaharmon
・・・
it’s hard to realize codependence is hurting you, when it’s so favored by the world around you.
. 
they will call you an angel, a savior even. they will only come to you, because you’re always there. when they are suffering, you are who they need. they know you will bail them out, take them back, take them in, easily forgive and forget. and they do this, not because they love you, but because you love them. more than they can.  more than yourself.  more than your own need to be truly loved.
. 
but then there comes a point where you have nothing left to give. 
you’re tired of not receiving what you need in life. you’ve done everything, changed and compromised yourself to the point of despair, and it’s still not enough. .
if this sounds familiar, please consider joining me in my soul family membership group this month.  we are doing a 5 part live coaching series on “ending codependence” for good.
. ⭐️ our first session begins this monday evening @8pm cst. .

you can attend the live session with me on facebook, where i can address your specific needs, or sign up for access to the archive.
.
register now and we can become better at love together. (link in bio.)
.
#soulfamilyvip #quote #codependence #relationships #dating #single #marriage #empath #artist #selfcare #lovingyourself #codependent #addiction #depression #narcissist, #relationship #inspiration #spiritjunkie #heal #metoo #spiritualgrowth

・・・
it’s hard to realize codependence is huing you, when it’s so favored by the world around you.
. 
they will call you an angel, a savior even. they will only come to you, because you’re always there. when they are suffering, you are who they need. they know you will bail them out, take them back, take them in, easily forgive and forget. and they do this, not because they love you, but because you love them. more than they can.  more than yourself.  more than your own need to be truly loved.
. 
but then there comes a point where you have nothing left to give. 
you’re tired of not receiving what you need in life. you’ve done everything, changed and compromised yourself to the point of despair, and it’s still not enough. .
if this sounds familiar, please consider joining me in my soul family membership group this month.  we are doing a 5 pa live coaching series on “ending codependence” for good.
. ⭐️ our first session begins this monday evening  cst. .

you can attend the live session with me on facebook, where i can address your specific needs, or sign up for access to the archive.
.
register now and we can become better at love together. (link in bio.)
.

text:
my name is r.c williams.

my #timesup and here i hang, castrated and raped with pinchers heated over a fire and forced into my anus.

because i was falsely accused of #rape .

after i was castrated, raped, and lynched they took turns shooting my body while hundreds of white people watched for entertainment.

i was later found innocent by a court, but my #timesupnow.

look at me and do not forget this lesson: false rape claims are just as prevalent as rape.

many men are falsely accused and then exonerated later and set free from prison.

even if rape was rampant, that would mean it would be easier to falsely accuse men of rape. and ironically and tragically enough, false rape claims can lead to prison rape. which is where rape culture term comes from.

it is not rare. american history and recent cases prove that false rape accusations happen. you can say that the amount looks low because not many people are found guilty of it. just like what people claim of rape.

remember this lesson from me:

innocent until proven guilty beyond reasonable doubt.

#drford #stopkavanaugh #fromlosinghisseatbecauseodfalseallegations
#kavanaughhearings #kavanaugh #ibelieveher #whensignificantevidenceisthefe #brettkavanaugh #nokavanaugh #isntguiltyofrape
#metoo #falselyaccused

text: i say this in parallel with great love, gratitude, and affection for the wonderful men in my life. i and other women need you right now, immediately. we need to hear your outrage alongside ours. we need you to speak out and speak up for us. we need to know you are doing something and saying something and not just wringing your hands. in some cases, our actual lives are at stake, and in all cases, our humanity and our rights are at stake. for all women - women of color, trans women, speak up now, before it's too late. please.* *please also do so without expecting a cookie, acknowledgment, reward, etc. because ain't nobody here got time for your conditional temporary or not intersectional feminism #believesurvivors #believewomen #timesup #metoo

text: this is 30. real talk: i plucked out two gray hairs today 😳 but it was seriously the best day! because i was surrounded by family and friends who love me, and reminded constantly even by those far away that i have so many people who care about me. it is such a humbling experience. because sometimes it is very easy to feel small and insignificant in this big big world 🌎 today i reflected on the fact that i feel so much better at 30 than i did when i was 20. i know who i am as a person; i am in way better shape!; my confidence and self assurance are off the charts in comparison! and we are living in a time where we are seeing significant cultural and sociological shifting. and i know sometimes it doesn’t feel very positive. there will always be upheaval, especially when real change is happening. this is the day for women! we are finding our voices, even amongst the chaos of the times, even amongst the people who want nothing more than to shut us down. and we get the amazing privilege to stand up and shout above the storm! wow babes, what a time to be alive. cheers to all! 🍻 and good night ❤️ #itsmybirthdayicansaywhatiwant #loveyou #thirtyflirtyandthriving #metoo #ibelieveher #stopkavanaugh

text:
👩‍❤️‍👩can you feel it? cuz i'm thinking of you and holding you close! 💓i'm bout to tell you all about the power i created while i healed from violence (spoiler alert, its #myfoodstampscookbook) - just a reminder to my tribe of revolutionary survivor and thrivers - i'm holding you in my heart while the fall of patriarchy is spiraling🌪.
.
.
tbh i've had to be mindful of my use of social media ☕️because of all the disclosures and emotions re #metoo 🤬. so while i cultivate the magical greatness i'm brewing over here, i am sending much #metta #lovingkindness in your direction 💫. and i want to shout from the mountain tops for you to click over to the book {link in bio} and reap the bennies from the work i did to heal for us.
.
.
i was looking for a good image 💻to use for this post and remembered i have this l have a freakin iibrary of stock images from the black woman-powered yoga studio in brooklyn. 🙏🏿🧘🏽‍♀️(peep ya girl hella skinny tho pre-motherhood! damn my body image journey is a whole nutha series i swear im gonna address)🤷🏽‍♀️ but yeah, i was in my 20s, post-trauma, in brooklyn to get far away from the bay where the perpetrators be at. and with the love and sisterhood of my #halfrican twin @tanyadiallok 🇨🇮we spread love the brooklyn way - swipe ➡️➡️➡️and just peep these gorgeous lovelies from the hip dhamma yoga studio. also, have you seen these pics before? cuz they hella popular images in the #blackyogi stock photo cannon... lol thank you to the talented @gregorycostanzo 📸🔥 .
.
.
and! heres some throwbacks from the early part of the journey to radical health- me tryna be cute with green smoothies n ish🥦💅🏽. from the archives! never give up, there's a gem at the bottom of every breakdown. i love you while we collectively witness.

text: sobering truth today. a woman was raped while riding her bike today on tower road by the park. at 10am. at a time when i think i’m perfectly safe to park my vehicle approximately where she was attacked and walk up to the field to run sprints. and i’m afraid to even admit that i’ve run there at night. as a survivor of an attempted assault, this shook me pretty hard today and made me reconsidering my options for where/how/when i run sprints. i consider myself to be pretty safe and i consider the risks at all times but this just reminded me of how vulnerable we can be at any moment. and to the men who follow this page, please take a deep breath and read this chart. it’s incredibly true what women are constantly considering. a pretty brave person i follow on instagram (@caleb_campbell) posted this & it felt super appropriate after reading about the attack yesterday. thanks for being empathetic and shining a light for those that don’t experience life the way that the ladies of the world do! be safe when you workout outdoors. be safe when you are walking into the gym. just be safe out there ladies. it could have easily been any of us. ♥️ #metoo #safetyfirst

text:
whenever a famous man gets accused of rape or assualt, two types of people come out of the woodwork; the "believe women" group, that will side with the woman no matter what, even if the whole thing is proven false. and the "innocent until proven guilty oh but the woman is automatically guilty of slander" group. we aren't judges or apart of the jury. we don't have to pick a side. we can be neutral until all the facts come out. "innocent until proven guilty" is there for both sides of the allegations. in the kavanaugh case, dr ford is innocent of perjury or slander until it's proven and kavanaugh is innocent of rape until it's proven. it's okay to be neutral. with new evidence coming out everyday, how could you already have your mind made up?

text:
one year ago, i made one of the hardest decisions of my life. i asked for help. i asked for help to walk away from an incredibly toxic and abusive relationship. a relationship that had consumed me and torn me apart. i started losing bits and pieces of myself without noticing. things that i loved were no longer important to me. .
the day i asked for help was a breath of fresh air. i am incredibly thankful not just for my family but to my friends, whom i admire immensely for stepping up and advocating for me, when i couldn't. .
the months afterward were filled with daily energy drinks, crying myself to sleep and a diagnosis of ptsd. i couldn't be alone or go anywhere by myself without having a panic attack. 
it has taken me a long time to openly talk about it without having to crack a joke to avoid crying. however, i've come along way. i was able to finish college, find an amazing job, and find a super cool apartment. i am able to say that i love my life. .
and that's why i'm sharing this. because it gets better. it got better. love is not being manipulated. love is not being hurt. love is not being bullied. love is a lot of things, but it's not abuse.
.
i've met so many wonderful people who have had experiences similar to mine and it's time for me to speak up. i had amazing people on my team and i'm on yours. whatever it is, i'm not judging. i'm here to listen. i'm here to love. i'm here to help. because it's important to know that you're not alone; there's many resources out there. i understand it's hard and scary but it gets better. you are an amazing person, who is loved and cherished. you deserve better.
.
.
.
.
.
.
#metoo #ibelieveher #love #support #women #empowerment #awareness #respect #loveisnot #domesticviolence #domesticviolenceawareness #pink

text:
fuck your vigil. fuck the bystander language used in promoting your vigil. as a survivor, i only feel pitied and ridiculed by lit candles and solemn faces. the vigil i need is one where we stop traffic. where we stand in the street with art and noise and music and uplift this collective grief. the vigil i need is one where men tell their #metoo stories, where they detail and describe the ways they have assaulted and have taken away the agency of another person. i need a vigil where men are solemn, shameful, and in their grief reflect on their somatic, bodily experience of when they assaulted. 
autumn brown said, "i'm never surprised when a man is accused of sexual assault. because, if you are a man, the most likely scenario is that you have behaved in an assaultive way towards someone... and it has nothing to do with your personality."

text:
this has been an intense week. the collective patriarchal political situation is big time stirring up the personal. my fb feed is filled with women sharing their sexual assault stories, by their fathers, boyfriends, bosses, teachers & explaining why they didn’t report, or the (nearly always) negative repercussions when they did.
.
women are reviewing their sexual & relationship histories & seeing that some of those “oops” moments weren’t actually oops at all - but moments where consent was overstepped. where a man put his pleasure before a women’s boundaries.
.
i’ve learned of 2 men who've repeatedly sexually (as well as mentally & emotionally) abused women so deeply they’ve been banned from the community & one has allegedly fled the country to avoid charges being pressed against him.
.
i talked with a woman friend today & we both were reeling in the realization of how deeply our lives have been shaped by the indiscretions & predatory aspects of men.
.
i had a better sex education than most thanks to my mom & my middle school, but i don’t recall once really learning about consent. do you?
.
what i now know is the absence of a no is not a yes. even a “yes” or “yeah, ok” is not a yes. a clearly stated with direct eye-contact fuck yes is a yes. anything less is a no. and if you’re not sure, it’s definitely a no.
.
but so much of this isn’t about consent - it’s about power. boys are taught to get their “manly” identity through dominating others. men who took that patriarchal conditioning in deeply don’t see women’s bodies or sexual contact through a lens of connection & consent, but through a lens of domination that reinforces their identities as “men.”
.
my prayer is this collective roar of women rising up & saying no will lead to a world where this toxic masculinity is no longer taught to boys. and girls will be taught to be fully expressed, not accommodating.
.
for now… if you’ve also been freshly reviewing your history & it’s rocking you, i want you to know: you are not alone. there’s light when we unpack our dark. keep going & get help if you need it.

text:
what’s october 3rd without a dash of pink? 💗 as much as i love pink, i wear a whole lot of navy. 🤪
.
colors aside, i’m sitting here at my work desk/craft station + trying not to keep my head in the news. (long post ahead...) i hardly share thoughts on political or my feelings about what’s happening the news. but these words from @ashhmarketing have been sticking close to me. resonating. important. worth sharing in a long post kinda words:
.
“phew. this last week has been a hard week.
.
everything happening at the senate has been triggering for me and - i know because i've personally talked to them - for many women around the country.
.
the amount of anger, powerlessness, and heartbreak within survivors and allies everywhere is overwhelming; it makes it difficult to get any actual work done.
.
and, although half of us want to scream until our throats are hoarse, we're starting a new week where we have to put a smile on our face and kick some ass because that's just what we have to do.”
.
this is one small, little post from my heart to yours. i admit, i feel like another statistic, another number buried under news reports of tragedy. sometimes i forget the humanity of these numbers... that those statistics are the faces + hearts of real people.
.
i didn’t post about the #metoo movement last year. my conversations around it was minimal honestly. sometimes i just don’t know how to dig in + sit in those conversations. they’re heavy. they’re painful. but what i do know is, despite what anyone may say or believe about your story: i see you. i hear you. you aren’t alone. i’m cheering you on in the overcoming, the fight + the bravery.
.
you aren’t just another statistic. you aren’t someone to be dismissed. you aren’t someone who caused this to happen.
.
if you need a safe space, a community to encourage you, this girl is in your corner. 💛 you are worthy. you are treasured. you are powerful. never forget that. ✨💕
name: pangshua  |  lue + riley

text:
tonight, i’m grateful that pittsburgh is basically a few streets and some buildings carved out of a giant forest. i’m never more than a 10-minute drive from a trail. and trails give me life, joy, peace, healing, grace, and restoration. there are days, like today, when my soul needs a little soothing. the woods never fail. 
but make no mistake. there is an element of fear every single time. i always watch who watches me walk into the woods. my camera is always on and every photo i take is uploaded to cloud storage. i record my routes on the alltrails app. one person has access to that data should they need it. two people have access to my phone’s location at all times. i alternate between breathing deeply and feeling bliss or looking around so i can see other people before they see me. i never listen to music so i can hear everything that is going on. i try to visit different trails on different days at different times. i wear shoes that support my crazy ankle in case i have to run. 
but even though this country is and has always been a “very scary” place for women in america, i will not stop going to the woods to soothe my soul and feed my breath. because i deserve life, joy, peace, healing, grace, and restoration. so do my daughters. so do you. #metoo

text: i think that now more than ever, it’s so important for women to stick together. to uplift, support, encourage, empathize, and listen to each other. to understand that feminism isn’t just about us, but about women across the world. it’s about you, your neighbor, your coworkers, your loved ones, women in history that didn’t have the rights we have now, and women in the future. i don’t know what lies ahead, but i know i want bright, fulfilling futures for the next generation of young girls. i want equal rights, equal pay, equal respect, equal trials, equal opportunities. and i want every woman reading this to know that you have a safe space with me. i am your ally, your supporter, your confidant, your motivator. i want the best for you, for women across the world, and for our future generation of warriors. if you ever need someone to talk to, i am here. if i follow or unknowingly interact/support your abuser, please let me know and i’ll immediately change that. if you just need an encouraging word when it feels like we’re losing the fight, i’m here. i know a lot of people are struggling with all that’s going on in the media right now, and i know it can be difficult to see sexual assault taken so lightly, so please just know, i am here. i support you. i care. #metoo

text:
logan shines for sexual violence awareness month 
the centre against sexual violence (casv) is lighting up all three logan water towers in teal and purple during sexual violence awareness month (svam). svam is held in october each year in queensland to raise community awareness about sexual violence, promote support options available for people who have been effected by sexual assault and to advocate that sexual violence cannot be tolerated in our communities. the logan water towers are located at jacaranda ridge in underwood, telfer st shailer park and the wineglass water tower in hillcrest. the towers will be lit up from the 1st-14th october, 2018. 
the casv is a community-based sexual assault service dedicated to providing counselling, education and information to the logan, beenleigh and redlands communities. the casv provides free, confidential and safe counselling and support to women and young women (12 years and over) effected by sexual assault. counselling and support is also provided to both women who would like assistance to access the national redress scheme. 
miranda clarke from the casv advised that, “we have a vision to eliminate sexual violence and encourage the community to join with us in working toward this goal.” she continued that “the casv is excited to shine a light on sexual violence across logan by lighting up the water towers”. you can also show your support by wearing a teal ribbon available free from the casv throughout the month of october to promote the elimination of sexual violence in our communities.

for further information please contact the casv – admin@casv.org.au, ph: 07 3808 3299. #respectmetoo #metoo #svam #qsan #watertower #sexualviolence #sexualassault #equality #awareness

text: i’ve been thinking a lot lately and doing some deep self reflection. it’s been hard for me to put how i’m feeling into words but i want to try so here it goes. these past five years have been both the best and hardest of my entire life. i have allowed other people to both inspire and bring me down. i’ve followed my heart and dreams even when it meant giving up things i loved along the way. i’ve struggled when trying to put myself first for the first time in my life because i lost people i was close to in the process. i’ve gone through a divorce and found a different kind of love that i had never experienced before. a love that is filled with honesty and given me the freedom to be who i am and be loved for it while still challenging me to be better. i’ve gone through a serious health scare that made me realize how short life can be. i’ve started my own company to not only share my passion with others but to help others achieve their dreams because i know how hard it is to have someone take a chance on you and believe/invest in you. i’ve left everything i’ve ever known behind to move cross country and experience something new. i’ve failed at some things but learned from them and have achieved many other things as a result. i’ve found the strength to share the truth about my past with the world only to find myself scared to share it again because of how some people reacted. i just keep reminding myself that i need to be strong for all those who can’t be so that they know they are not alone and that there is hope. i’m refusing to let the labels that society wants to place on me define me and it is my hope for all those that i love to do the same. so if you are someone who wants to pass judgement on me for being divorced or having bpd as a result of being sexually abused then please do both of us a favor and feel free to unfollow me. 👋🏻 the world today is a scary place with too much hate and judgement and not enough love, understanding, and compassion. i wanted to take a break from my social media highlight reel to be vulnerable and share some raw emotions on a day that is a hard one for me. #metoo

text:
cristano ronaldo volta a negar acusação de estupro e diz ter a consciência tranquila 
o jogador cristiano ronaldo, da juventus, voltou a negar em suas redes sociais as acusações de que teria estuprado a americana kathryn mayora em um hotel de las vegas em 2009. “nego terminantemente as acusações de que sou alvo. considero a violação um crime abjeto, contrário a tudo aquilo que sou e em que acredito. não vou alimentar o espectáculo midiático montado por quem quer se promover à minha custa”, disse o português em mensagem publicada em sua conta no twitter.

em entrevista publicada na última sexta (28) pela revista alemã der spiegel, a americana kathryn mayorga, 34, acusa o jogador da juventus de a ter estuprado em junho de 2009, depois que os dois se conheceram em uma casa noturna.

no início do ano seguinte, foi assinado um acordo no qual cristiano ronaldo se comprometeu a pagar us$ 375 mil (r$ 1,5 milhão em valores atuais) à suposta vítima, que, por sua vez, nunca mais falaria sobre o ocorrido.

no entanto, após trocar de advogado e ver a repercussão do movimento #metoo, no qual mulheres contam histórias de abusos sofridos, ela decidiu falar sobre o caso.

depois de mayorga ter divulgado novas informações sobre o caso, a polícia de las vegas decidiu na última segunda (1º) reabrir a investigação contra cristiano ronaldo por estupro. (…) @ta_na_net_tnn 
#ta_na_net_tnn 
#tnnoficial

text:
** two more weeks**
🌿 spots still available🌿 
f i n d i n g  y o u r  v o i c e 
workshop/support group for women adult survivors of sexual assault/abuse. 🌟
when - october 17th, four wednesdays, skipping the 31st, from 6:00-8:00 ⭐️ where- mariner’s church, life development building, room 200 a 🌟 $25 pre registration required ✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨having your voice when you have experienced sexual abuse is one of the most difficult and most courageous things a survivor can do. before you have your voice, you have to find your voice. sexual abuse, insult, or assault is damaging to the body, mind, and soul; the voice gets buried under many layers within. the aim of this group is to help heal, restore, and recover the lost places so that you can find and have your voice, your thoughts, your feelings, your boundaries, and to discover that you’re not so bad after all. ❤️
🙏
through education, processing, art therapy, yoga and breath work, this will be a time to set the silence and shame free, and find the refreshed and strong you that’s been there all along. 
dm me if you’re interested, or visit the care and recovery page on marinerschurch.org and follow the link for support groups. 
#findingyourvoice #healing #hope #metoo #womensvoices #recovery #supportgroup #survivor #iamworthy #therapy #therapygroup #therapistvibes #anniebroggertherapy #findingyourvoice

text:
pretty soon most of my sessions will be divided into the true exploration of the tantric path and tantra for what i experienced amazing benefits for, that being trauma and situations that damage fragments of ourselves and cause blockages in development. 
for women my focus is on the fact that when women's liberation occured it simply was delivered with not an ounce of direction or help which led us to where we are today. 
being sexually liberated means you have a choice. means you  empower yourself to unfold unveil your nature because we are equals. 
the sacred masculine can not and would not exist without the divine feminine
and vice versa
why? because we are in polarity. 
simple. equal. 
trauma in any form causes great impact to our development and our true unfolding. "despite the human capacity to survive and adapt, traumatic experiences can alter  people’s psychological, biological, and social equilibrium to such as degree that  the memory of one particular event comes to taint all other experiences, spoiling  appreciation of the present'(van der kolk, & macfarlane, 2007, p. 4). this and more going up soon in today's blog later
while in flight might as well do the content writing. 🤣😎🤗 tantricjourneys.tumblr.com

text:
“charm is deceptive and beauty is fleeting, but a woman who fears the lord [regards him in great awe] will be praised.” proverbs 31:30
📖
hey she is fam! this past summer i noticed something that i haven’t really paid attention to in the past: white butterflies. and almost everyday i’d see two or four of them. no more. no less. i looked up the significance of a white butterfly. they represent the intricate and fragile lace of us—our femininity. i watched one once frantically weaving and twirling in the wind trying to make its way from one place to the next. and looking back on it, it reminded me of she is.
🤔
we are fragile, intricately made beings—beautifully made inside and out, with nothing but greatness in mind. and when we’re met with the winds of life, we can lose sight of that. we can lose sight of our beauty. our purpose. our identity.
🙈
the winds can get great. and we can feel like we’re being controlled by them instead of strategically maneuvering in them. and often times the wind can ground us. they can be so toilsome that we’re forced to the ground in what it seems like defeat. but we have the wingspan of angels, family. and we have the strength to soar even though we’re looking at the ground…for the moment. we’re meant to fly above the weight of the wind—the world, the culture, the hurts we’ve faced, the residual pain from the past. the grounding, if we let god guide us in it, will only make our wings stronger. you want to read the rest don't ya?👇🏽 {for the rest of this sweet devotional visit our website, link in our bio!} {pintrest photo}
.
.
.

#whitebutterfly #cocoon #fly #makeithappen #progressnotperfection 
#gospelofgrace #hopespoken #bethevoice #cagednomore #metoo 
#womanonamission #youdoyou #iamenough #forhisglory #preachergirl 
#makehisnameknown #amen

text:
after never receiving official written clearance to perform a thorough investigation, and with severe restrictions imposed by the white house, more than forty people with credible information on kanvanaugh have not been interviewed by the fbi. 
neither ford nor kavanaugh have been re-questioned. 
and yet the (sham) fbi report is expected tonight. 
the day following disgustingly mocking comments at the expense of dr. ford, a sexual assault survivor, by the president of the united states, a report will be generated that will most likely pave the way for an unqualified, entitled, and highly biased potential predator to sit on the highest court of the land. 
where did our country go?

i pray that jeff flake, susan collins, and other republicans gather the courage to choose integrity over politics and vote no on kavanaugh. 
and i pray that heart/centered individuals who truly love and value this country will get out and vote in november.  enough.
#stopkavanaugh #believesurvivors #ibelievedrford #timesup #metoo

text:
the one i got the most was “you shouldn’t dress that way because you will provoke men”
no....women should be allowed to walk, talk, dress and act how they like without being harassed by little boys who don’t know the definition of what it means to be a man! 😡
the way i dress should not determine your hands touching me!
if i’ve had to much to drink....put me in a cab and send me home. (don’t take advantage)
if things get heated and i say no....it means no!
women made this #metoo movement to make a statement.
.....
i was a victim of sexual assault as a child.
i’ve heard all the sick perverted disgusting “jokes” that men make all the time and am forced to sit there and laugh at things that are really....not that funny!
telling a woman that she is “too emotional” because she reacts to something you say and doesn’t agree or gets upset, that’s wrong!
we are emotional beings, yes.
but we are also, kind, loving, nurturing,caring, strong, brave, smart, funny, innovators, motivators, mothers, sisters, daughters, aunts, grandmas.
women are and always will be just as good as men!
as james brown put it~ this is a mans world, but it wouldn’t be nothing without a woman or a girl.
....
so hold your head up high ladies, fight for every right you know you deserve. do not stand there and tolerate rudeness or misogyny. you are better than that! 
remember that you are beautiful and you are loved, and god made you fearfully and wonderfully made 💪🏼😊❤️😘#womenareamazing #girlpower #nomeansno #standupagainstsexualassault #womenarepeopletoo #youarebeautiful

even my dog knows no means no! #metoo #believeher 
rowan & i protested kavanaugh and rape culture today. hear my truth, enough is enough. we aren't objects, we don't exist to make you happy, we don't owe you a thing. if you don't stand for something, you'll fall for anything. what is more important than standing for the right to your body and the right to be heard? we should be screaming, to those in power, you will hear us. hear our cries, our pain, because we're breaking the silence now.

text: shout out to everyone showing up and doing the work right now, even though it’s often soul crushing, uncomfortable, and exhausting. this moment in time has been particularly galvanizing for women (and white women have started showing up when they haven’t before) - but it’s incredibly important that we stay engaged and keep showing up, even when the issue at hand doesn’t directly apply to you or your experience. we have to remember that our fight doesn’t end with the kavanaugh nomination, no matter which way it goes. it is more comfortable to stay home. it is more comfortable to wrap yourself in your privilege, stay silent, and wait for someone else to speak up. but we have a collective responsibility to create the kind of world we want to live in (and a world that others want to live in) and complacency can’t be an option anymore. i’m eternally grateful for anita hill’s courage, and we can all use it as a guiding light this week, and the next, and the next #thesweetfeminist

text:
the princess of the sea

there once lived a girl, as mysterious as the night. as clear as glass yet, as soft as snow inside.
she met a guy of fire; of coal black eyes.
 with his words of molten chocolate, he beckoned her by his side like a fire to a moth and like the foolish old insect, she too was charred.

tossing and turning through the splinters of her heart, she took them all. pieces of love and feelings; of care and emotions galore. she took them all and wove a warning for her soul.

feelings break you down; like a flower she would be no more.
be the thorn or the snake by the lake. be the fierce mountain lion with his gilded gold mane.
 but feel no more. let no words melt the snow of her soul- to unthawable ice it changed. and then she moved; like the brave princess of the sea. through the cruel dark world, herself; she’s free.

coz they lie and they break, every promise that they make. it’s not true she said. it’s better never to have-  than to have loved… and left. -phoenix aquain♥️
.
.
.
.

text:
i've debated these past few days whether or not to post this. i've decided to share and though it is a very personal thing to be open and vulnerable.. sometimes people need to see your vulnerability for them to feel comfortable to be vulnerable themselves. 
#whyididntreport 
because i blamed myself even though i said no
because i was scared 
because there was a drug involved even though i didn't want to i was afraid what that would mean for me 
because i felt dirty 
but mostly because i thought it was my fault. 
my story didn't end there. by gods grace! 
for years i looked to god asking why god?! why me, why that. why couldn't i just forget it or die.
but god.... romans 5:8 says "but god shows his love for us in that while we were sinners christ died for us." god showed me his love. i can look back now without asking "why god" in all that has happened in my life but say "thank you god" for allowing me to live and to opening my eyes to see you! praise god for he has been patient with me that i might come to repentance and through that repentance i have been reconciled to my heavenly father.

text:
is ignorance really bliss? silence is not always golden.

the land of the free and the home of the brave is also the same place where the president (donald trump) can find comfort living in stupidity and ignorance by making fun of someone that is a victim of sexual assault. the lack of sensitivity is sickening and disheartening. 
you do not have to remember every single part of an event to remember that you were negatively affected. domestic violence and sexual assault of men and women are a part of a plague...an epidemic.

what does it take for you to believe that someone (that you know) was assaulted or abused?

how unfair and horrific it is that people that are labeled as leaders are allowed to behave is such undignified and disgusting ways. are we as a society paying attention to how this behavior is creating a trickling/domino effect starting with leaders and working its way down to everyday people? since when is it okay to make fun of someone (in any setting) while your supporters applaud you and laugh at the victim?

do you stand for something or are you just sitting and watching the circus-like event applauding in the background with the clowns? 
your truth matters and i believe you. can you guess why? as a survivor-turned-warrior, i stand for those who do not have a voice. i stand for those who may have lost themselves because of pain or fear. i stand for those who don't know how to leave. i stand for those who have lost their lives because of assault, abuse, rape, etc. i stand for all people that are ignored or made fun of because of their story and their truth. i stand for all people that are subjected to abuse/assault and forever will i stand. i offer my love and my support to anyone that may need me or the services offered by breaking the silence against domestic violence.

still don't know why i stand up and i am speaking out? i do so, because i am a survivor!!! #domesticviolenceawareness #rawtruthdv #kaylaspositivitycorner #awareness #ibelieveher #ibelievesurvivors #imasurvivor #truthmatters #overcomingabuse #ignoranceisnotbliss #whatsyourtruth #healthandwellness #metoo

text:
weinstein, cosby, kavanaugh. a fire has been lit and though it may seem to scorch our earth, it also ushers in a newfound fertility. that’s why we must embrace this fire and let it burn— allow its flames to lick at our wounds, to ignite the pain, the shame, the rage unsung and stir the ashes that once buried it.
.
as a survivor of multiple sexual assaults, i found myself quietly weeping with dr. ford— old tears mixed with new ones. painful memories, long since healed, were being nudged to life. and not just my own memories; i was feeling for all of us—tapped into the collective memory held in my cells—my lineage, our lineage, thousands of years of sexual violence against women. and i, the prey and the predator, the innocent and the guilty. for i too held my tongue and surrendered my power. i too changed my behavior and my outfit—for them or to hide from them—the good girl, the slut, the tomboy. i too shamed the feminine and cast her out of me.
.
this wasn’t a new awareness for me. i had sought out this healing before and even cycled completely through it. heck, i just wrote about it for my next book! (which sent me on yet another cycle of healing but... more on that later) the point is, i had full on shamanized it and yet there i was— weeping. and i know i wasn’t alone. many of us wept— for her, for ourselves, for each other and even for him. some were triggered into their trauma while others felt the rage of wanting to defend that pain, to condemn it and castrate it.
.
whatever you felt, my invitation to you is to put down your sword and sit with the fire for a bit. let it work its magic on you. the very patriarchy that we seek to unseat is the same force that tells us to ignore these emotions, to bypass them, or to channel them into “productive” action. but we must embrace our emotions if we are to truly heal. this is why so many survivors of sexual abuse stand atop a victim who hasn’t yet healed. this is our calling back to her, to honor her voice—just as we did dr. ford’s—and to let her have the floor.
🔥🌹🔥
#emotionalhealing #traumahealing #shamansister

text:
october is national domestic violence awareness month. every day thousands of americans of every race, colour, creed, gender, sexual orientation, socioeconomic status and age experience domestic violence. not all victims have visible wounds, in fact, one of the most insidious parts of domestic violence are the scars no one can see. 
love does *not* hurt. there is help. you are not alone. you are not crazy. it's not your fault. 
learn more about domestic violence. find help & healing. when we break the silence, together we can end the cycle of domestic violence. 
national child abuse hotline
1.800.422.4453
www.childhelp.org
national domestic violence hotline
1.800.799.7233
www.ndvh.org
rape, abuse & incest national network
1.800.656.4673
www.rainn.org
national teen dating abuse helpline
1.866.331.9474
www.loveisrespect.org
national suicide prevention lifeline
1.800.273.8255

text_retweet:
#repost @pacificschoolofreligion
・・・
in the age of the #metoo movement and these days following the testimony of dr. christine blasey ford, when national attention is being drawn to the stories of women and others who experience and sometimes report their own experience surviving domestic abuse and sexualized violence, it is vital for people—particularly people of faith—to rise up and respond with compassion for those who have experienced violence to their bodies, minds, and spirits and with meaningful action to transform the injustices of patriarchy and misogyny that undergird this systemic violence.
.
we know that many in our community have been impacted by sexualized violence in so many different ways. for some of us, these have been difficult days of triggering, anger and sadness. so, it is also vital for each of us to consider how we empower survivors to shape the narratives of what constitutes justice, meaningful action, and healing.
.
we are also aware that many folks—wounded healers, resilient fighters, and transformation seekers alike—have been holding space for those who are feeling the effects of experiences of sexualized violence, triggering, and retraumatization.
.
and many of us have been experiencing all of those things, sometimes in the midst of our callings to care for others.
.
so we want you to know—wherever in the world you are—we believe you, we are holding space for you, we are praying for you.
.
you are believed. you are beloved. you are seen. you are held by this community and in the heart of the holy. .
.
text adapted from words by @sharon_fennema.
photo by @thetoddwhitley from tuesday’s @pacificschoolofreligion community worship, “believed and beloved: worship for the breaking”
name: todd atkins-whitley

i believe that women deserve so much better than what's available in the fitness world.  you deserve to be seen and heard.  to be treated with dignity.  not put in a box and told to plod along on a treadmill or elliptical for hours on end, never touching a weight heavier than your purse for fear of getting "bulky". here's what i know from my own journey and from working with hundreds of women:  lifting kettlebells is the fastest, safest, most effective way to get stronger in mind, body, and spirit. 😊💪🙏 if you're interested in finding out more, sign up for a free intro to kettlebells class here:  http://sisustrengthlab.com/book-online

if you aren't in the summerville, sc area, i can meet with you online.  give me a call or shoot me a message.💜 it's gonna be awesome! 🙌

text: i often don’t like being vulnerable. if you know me you know i like to put on a tough exterior. partly because i learned to and partly because i don’t like to show my emotions. i feel like someone needs this so i’m letting down my walls and being vulnerable!  last #metoo movement i was fearful of being vulnerable. i didn’t want people to judge me and look at me different. thing is sexual assault/abuse isn’t something we should hide behind. i know, we often hide for fear of being judged, fear of people not believing, fear of people not caring, fear of telling people you trust brushing it under the rug to avoid conflict, fear of repercussions.  there is freedom waiting! is it easy? absolutely not! do i still struggle? absolutely. but what i do know is you are strong, you are loved, you are beautiful, you matter, i’m listening and i hear you! #metoo #speakup #stopsexualabuse

هزاران دلال و تاجرهای سعودی و اماراتی که عرب هستند دلال های خودشوتو ریختن تو بازار هر قیمتی بگی ارز را می خرند هر قیمتی بگی!!!! این داستان حالا حالا ادامه داره این شیوه عرب که عرب امارات و سعودی هستند میلیاردها دلار کنار گذاشتند و میگویند ما فکر میکنیم که موشک خریدیم و با ایران در حال جنگیم آین هم یک مدل جنگ هست .

text: oh girl, you’re only scratching the surface of heart breaks.  your hormones are raging as you enter your early teenage years and you crush on a different boy almost every week.  you’re starting to seek relationships with boys to make up for what you never had with your father.  i wish you were aware of this as it would save you from a lot of random hook-ups and time spent with men who don’t deserve you.  no man can make up for the lack of attention, comfort and love in your relationship with your father. you will find that the more fulfilled you feel internally, the harder it will be for any guy to break your heart because you won’t put up with any b.s.  you’ll know what you deserve and you’ll demand nothing less.  and guess what?  once you get there, you’re going to meet someone who will love and cherish you like you’ve always imagined.  you’re a stubborn one though, so it’ll be another 26 years before he comes into your life.  but in the mean time, focus on yourself.  comfort yourself.  love yourself.  and most importantly, protect yourself.

text:
recent events with the kavanaugh trials have shed a lot of light on the #metoo movement and inspired a new hashtag, #whyididntreport. christine blasey ford accused brett kavanaugh, supreme court nominee, of sexual assault in high school. their hearings took place on thursday and the senate judiciary committee will vote on kavanaugh’s nomination this week. currently, the fbi is investigating the charges. 
1 in 6 women and 1 in 33 men have been victims of attempted or completed rape, which is a traumatic experience for anyone. studies show that the prevalence of false reporting is between 2% and 10%, and claims can be labeled “false” easily due to inconsistent circumstances.

text:
first of all thank you @averywilde for being one of my closest friends for the past 15 plus years and for being my gay husband. you have always been a role model to me. the fact that you have overcome every obstacle being a gay man of color and being able to succeed in new york is just beyond me, it’s heroic the fact that you are 100 percent selfmade and you had just about every challenge anyone can face and you managed to defeat them all and find success and love in this world. you inspire me so much so that i dedicate this song #bitch by #meredithbrooks to you because you said it’s been your favorite song to karaoke to. i loved this song for being poignant in the 90’s, but i love it even more now being 40 and a woman in business. it also seems apropos because of the #metoo movement and the latest trial with #brettkavanaugh and #christineblaseyford #imwithher btw.. duh? i’m also super pumped to read #rebeccatraister new book “good and mad” the revolutionary power of woman’s anger because #imabitch #imalover #imachild #imamother and i hate the world today
you're so good to me
i know but i can't change
tried to tell you
but you look at me like maybe
i'm an angel underneath
innocent and sweet
yesterday i cried
must have been relieved to see
the softer side
i can understand how you'd be so confused
i don't envy you
i'm a little bit of everything
all rolled into one
i'm a bitch, i'm a lover
i'm a child, i'm a mother
i'm a sinner, i'm a saint
i do not feel ashamed
i'm your hell, i'm your dream
i'm nothing in between
you know you wouldn't want it any other way
so take me as i am
this may mean
you'll have to be a stronger man
rest assured that
when i start to make you nervous
and i'm going to extremes
tomorrow i will change
and today won't mean a thing

i do not feel ashamed

i'm nothing in between

just when you think, you got me figured out
the season's already changing
i think it's cool, you do what you do
and don't try to save me

i'm a child, i'm a mother
i'm a sinner, i'm a saint

text: my face after i told my mom my story. my whole story. my #metoo moments (yes there’s more than one). i feel a sense of relief and yet a serious heavy ness is surrounding me. what is going on in our country? i hope we are heading in the right direction but i feel overwhelmed by the news every day. i’m not looking for sympathy- i’m attempting to inspire others to be brave. share your stories and don’t be scared. i’m here if anyone ever needs to talk and i will listen. not because i’m a democrat, not because i’m nice but because i’m a human and a woman and a kind hearted lady that is no longer willing to shut up and take it. i also know how hard life can be and i am not sitting down anymore. women must get better at standing up for themselves. i can’t thank my mama enough for asking me at dinner tonight “so i heard a story on the radio today that said 9 in 10 daughters don’t tell their parents about their #metoo sexual experiences. do you have a #metoo moment?”. i don’t know why i didn’t tell her sooner but i don’t think it matters. she knows now and we sat and cried together. it’s really nice to know i have someone as amazing as her in my life. i’m so happy you started this conversation mama because i never would have. love you more than words can say @nananormandie. #metoo #momsareangelsonearth #wemustdobetter #healingprocess #vote
name: Caitlin Davies

text:
i believe that women deserve so much better than what's available in the fitness world.  you deserve to be seen and heard.  to be treated with dignity.  not put in a box and told to plod along on a treadmill or elliptical for hours on end, never touching a weight heavier than your purse for fear of getting "bulky". here's what i know from my own journey and from working with hundreds of women:  lifting kettlebells is the fastest, safest, most effective way to get stronger in mind, body, and spirit. 😊💪🙏 if you're interested in finding out more, sign up for a free intro to kettlebells class here:  http://sisustrengthlab.com/book-online

if you aren't in the summerville, sc area, i can meet with you online.  give me a call or shoot me a message.💜 it's gonna be awesome! 🙌

text:
to my beautiful mother, i am sorry for the mistreatment you have received under the current sheriff’s administration which has been horrible, unfair, and unnecessary. as officers, you are all held to a higher standard. while you have done your part in this, others have not. and yet you were punished for speaking up as you are required. you were prevented from promoting. you were denied the right to better yourself and provide for your family the way you should be able to. you, a strong, courageous woman, were beaten down to the last ounce of fight you had in you to finally speak out about these injustices. they got to retire early to avoid repercussions, they got to turn you into the bad guy for things you spoke out about, they got to promote and provide for their families without any regard for what their actions did to us. our family. i am sorry that stan sniff and his good ole boys club, filled with pathetic pussies, allowed this to happen. but i am proud of you. i am inspired and in awe of your courage to stand up and fight these motherfuckers. you are nothing short of a phenomenal and amazing woman. i love you mom, we will win this fight for you, for us, and for others experiencing similar misconduct. 💛

please, make a difference and go vote for chad bianco in the upcoming elections. share my moms story, let them know we know and that we’re sick of it. thank you. #metoo
