text:
back in the saddle today and hot damnnnnnnnn did it feel good! albeit i was on a spin bike next to my partner in crime, bob getting my ass handed to me by my favorite instructor so it wasn’t this scenic!
😆🚴🏻‍♀️🔥
honestly after class i was pretty emotional. i pushed hard and my endurance fitness has a longgggg way to go but i freaking did it. i showed up and worked hard and laughed/joked around with bob about donuts and simply did it!
•
it’s incredible to me how much fitness and our sport can parallel the situations in our lives. at points i could barely breathe and i had some flashbacks to anxiety taking my breath away. it was offputting at first and i had fleeting thoughts of “i don’t want to do this and feel breathless”. it was a little triggering for me to be real. but i grounded myself quickly and reminded my head, heart and breath that i could breathe right now. that actually all i had to do in this very moment was spin on a bike and sweat. i looked over to bob and he was working hard and it made me smile. i was safe. i was doing what i love. so i took a few of the deepest breaths i had and screamed in my head that i was stronger than anxiety and stronger than i even knew. i screamed “yes you can” just as my instructor was yelling at us. i screamed, you can and are doing something hard and scary in real life and that can translate to doing really hard workouts. i felt relief and pushed more.
•
i think a big reason i took so much time off triathlon this season is how scary i knew it would be in my own head and also that i didn’t want to feel breathless. today was a huge step for me. overcoming and proving to myself just how far i have come. i was in a dark room. sweating my ass off. singing out loud to the music. working hard. and safe next to one of my best friends of my lifetime. it was all just perfect. and i felt so happy after. like something was released and let go. ahhhhhhhhhh i just felt lighter!
💓💖💓
anyways, i’ve never been one that get caught up in chasing numbers, podiums or prs. i’m totally cool if that’s your thing but seeing this picture from ironman wisconsin last year simply reminds me that i’m in triathlon to chase down that smile. 😊

text: ponto prévio: não faço ideia se ronaldo é inocente ou não da acusação que agora lhe fazem de ter violado uma mulher em 2009. se for culpado que seja, evidentemente, exemplarmente punido. ele ou seja quem for. o que acho escandaloso é ver como, em larga escala, o movimento #metoo ameaça neste momento os mais elementares direitos cívicos de qualquer cidadão como o sejam nomeadamente a presunção de inocência. mesmo que judicialmente, até ver, essa presunção de inocência esteja garantida, já nada limpará a imagem e o bom nome de cr7, como de diversas outras pessoas que têm sido acusadas ao longo do último ano. neste caso, choca-me ainda mais ver como basta um testemunho (sem qualquer prova apresentada até ao momento) de uma pessoa que ninguém sabe quem é, 9 anos após os alegados factos, para fazer tremer, com uma violência que nem o fisco espanhol nem messi alguma vez conseguiram, o império construído ao longo de 15 anos por cr7. e isso parece-me potencialmente injusto, mas seguramente precipitado e irresponsável. um anónimo tem de se sentir suficientemente respaldado pelas instituições para poder acusar quem quer que seja. é nisso que assenta o estado de direito. mas jamais em caso algum se pode inverter o ónus da prova. não é ronaldo que tem de provar a sua inocência. é esta senhora (que apresentou uma queixa, mas não identificou o agressor, que aceitou dinheiro para ficar calada e que agora vem violar o silêncio que se comprometeu a cumprir no acordo que terá assinado) que tem de provar que foi violada por cr7.  mais me choca ainda ver que na linha da frente de quem se apressa a apontar o dedo a ronaldo (e indirectamente ao futebol) está muita gente por manifesto preconceito intelectual e social. termino como comecei: não faço a menor ideia se ronaldo violou esta senhora, ou não. se o fez que seja condenado e que sinta toda a censura social inerente à prática de um crime sexual. mas uma coisa eu sei: uma pessoa que foi violada, não identifica o agressor (por favor poupem-me ao argumento de que achava que ninguém ia acreditar nela e de que ronaldo era demasiado poderoso), aceita dinheiro para ficar calada e passados 9 anos aproveita a crista da onda para violar

- - [ t h i s  for  t h a t ] - -

so much hype around the last 90 days of the year... and i love❤ the new found energy⚡ from everyone. but, for me, i feel like this entire year has been a time of reflection💎. .
.
.
every month i can look back to the year prior and think to myself, 'wow... you did that?!' 'overcame that shit.' 'that was tough, hope that never happens again!!' 'can't wait to do that again!!'
.
.
.
all in all, i'm left proud... still 90 days out📆. cause i'm still trying. and thats all we can do, right?! hard to see that unless you reflect👓!!
.
.
.
i've struggled personally most of this year, big transistion period✌. so going into the next 90 days with gratitude for the 9 months prior😍.
.
.
💋if you knew me, you would know.... i let go of a business that was never really a business. hardest part was overcoming/stopping the self punishment i inflicted on myslef for being a 'quitter'. p.s. honoring the next right thing does not make you a quitter. garuntee you will use something you learned✌
.
.
💋if you knew me, you would know.... learning [ still learning ] what success is to me and how i determine my self worth. it's a process #forsure. 
p.s. success does not always come in titles and in money. i need to remind myself this daily✌
.
.
💋if you knew me, you would know.... that i've struggled accepting my body in all its weight gains & the biggest acceptance struggle is, adjusting to these new 'boobs'. #scarsarebeautiful 
p.s. i punish my body with food [ pizza every other day is too much]. i punish my body with too much negative putdowns. but, my body hasn't gave up on me and it's time i respect her and all she has endured and continues to endure and quit being such a rude house guest✌
.
.
so... here i am, determined to get it right every day. but, most days i feel like i fail🤦‍♀️ #samesiessister. i struggle with creating a schedule and finding my purpose daily🤷‍♀️.
.
.
i'm gonna focus my energy on letting the pressure go of my expectations and gaining the love for the moment. .
.
a this for that method😘

text:
when you are made a victim against your will, it has a life long affect. i'm busy creating my life and don't think about it much....except when i sit in silence, appreciating the innocence of my own children. i vowed to be strong enough to keep them safe even before they were born. i'm fiercely protective of my kids because i've lived through childhood sexual, physical and emotional abuse up to age 6.  i am hyper aware of everything. 
now, my daughter is now almost the age i was when i was punched in the face by a man with his closed fist and made to look down as he talked about gang raping me. there are still more stories that i do not wish to share.  i want better for them. so, call me an advocate or a survivor or whatever...but, i don't live there. i live in the possibility of now and of what is to come. i live happily and confidently....yet carefully. #metoo

text: one of my #favorite #freestyle #fridays from #keynote #poets #sacramento with the ☝🏻 and only @poetmichaelellis ... i am going to be real honest... existing this week has been brutal and it is only wednesday y'all😔 ... the attacks on the female experience by the #kavanaugh trials and other cases that have been brought to the forefront of the media cycle through the #metoo campaign has been exhausting to my physical, emotional, and psychological self... even my spirit hurts... i am deeply saddened by the men around me and in the media.. i understand that just like white folks, men too are conditioned and socialized to be the oppressor and blinded by their biases... yet, i urge the men around me to listen to the ladies around them, especially womxn of color who deal with both racism and sexism. i understand not all men are rapists, bad human beings, etc.. just like not all white folks are horrible ppl either.. but saying, "well womxn rape too," or "womxn shouldn't allow their daughters to wear yoga pants if they don't like how men behave," is not that different than justifying the actions of white folks who perpetuate racism in our culture or say all lives matter... there is a level of #power, #privilege, and #intersectionality missing from the dialogue. my #heart goes out to my fellow #femme identified folks who are being retraumatized through this process.. you ladies and the men who have been speaking out in #solidarity are the true #warriors and #healers of our communities... and i thank you for your bravery as we continue to fight. an attack on any disadvantaged community is an attack on all disadvantaged communities #womxn, #lgbtq, #immigrants, #poc, etc... #much #love #blessings and #healing i send to you all this week. please take care of yourselves🌻🌙✨

text:
in absolute defiance of the innumerable assaults on my human sovereignty granted to me by birthright; i have entered the country of turkey.

i am jewish. i am from the united states of america. i am a hardcore crust punk. i am anti-imperialist. i am anti-fascist. i am anti-authoritarian. i am pro-love. i am pro-immigration. i am pro-choice. i believe in dignity for all. i stand firm against abusers. i believe in free and protected expression of sexuality and gender expression. i believe in feminism. i believe in god. i am willing to fight for human rights and liberty for all. i am anti-corruption. i am anti capital punishment. i am pro-union. i believe in equal rights for all (every race, religion, skin tone, country of origin, lgbtq+, immigration status, body shape, gender...) i support the decriminalization of drugs, i believe in harm reduction,  i believe psychiatry is  violence,  i support whistleblowers, i believe in quality free healthcare for all. i believe survivors.  i believe in restorative justice, i support alternate methods of healing, i support safe injection sites, i support cannabinoids and natural healing.

i believe in cooperation over competition. i believe that people are more important than profit. i believe that animals and the environment deserve respect.  i support sex-workers. i respect truth-tellers, i believe those who are accused deserve to properly be defended and those who claim they have been harmed deserve to properly be heard and state their case. i believe black lives matter.  i believe big pharma is criminal. i believe poverty is violence. i support civil and criminal lawsuits against those who abuse power. i support justice for trauma survivors. 
i support #metoo. i believe all survivors deserve extra chances to make amends. i believe all survivors are desperate in ways that may impact their judgement. i believe in ethical anarchism. i believe in forgiveness.  i believe that lyme disease is real. i believe in mutual aid.  i denounce the dsm. i support bdsm.  i support birth control for men and shared responsibility. if she, he or they say no or stop, even if you are about to *** then you stop. 
i support good food for all.

text_retweet:
#repost @gracieandrachel with @get_repost
・・・
her
———
on the morning of thursday, september 27th, 2018, an eager anticipation woke us up in our brooklyn loft unusually early. with our hearts racing, we tuned into the hearings of dr. christine blasey ford and judge brett kavanaugh.
———
amidst dr. ford’s emotionally brave testimony, kavanaugh’s flippant denial, and an amalgamation of statements from an assembly of both incredibly compassionate and unbelievably ruthless senators, we made a new song. and it was for her.
———
once the hearings were over, we began putting a video together to more fully capture the inspiration behind this song. we wanted to point to women, from a range of walks of life, women who have taken a stance when it wasn’t necessarily easy to do so. our goal was to highlight the courage it takes to call something out loud and to stand up tall when the odds may not be in our favor.
———
the women in this piece are just a few among many who inspire us to continue to use our voices and demand to be heard. the conclusory chorus lyric “never look back again” doesn’t imply we shouldn’t look back on the women who have taught us how to lead the way — we most absolutely should — but that we should always move bravely into the future. we hope with our song to thank the women who have empowered us so selflessly and perhaps to inspire those still searching to find their strengths.
———
see the full video for “her” now! link in bio.
———

#drford #metoo #ibelieveher #nokavanaugh #cancelkavanaugh #istillbelieveanitahill #taranaburke #wcw #wce

handcuffed and blinded
.
most of us were relieved when senator jeff flake called for an fbi investigation before he’d vote to confirm judge brett kavanaugh to the supreme court. although trump said he wanted a “comprehensive” fbi investigation, we now know that’s just another trump lie. in truth, the fbi has been severely restricted both in time and especially in scope. they’ve only interviewed four witnesses and each step the fbi might want to take has to be okayed by trump.
.
more than 40 people with potential information into the allegations against kavanaugh haven’t been contacted for interviews. one accuser, deborah ramirez, has given the fbi a list of more than 20 people she said either heard about later or were witnesses to brett kavanaugh exposing himself to her while drunk at a college party. none of these people have been contacted. there are potential witnesses who are attempting to contact the fbi no avail. the investigation is wrapping up and the senate judiciary committee is waiting the report now. this whole reality-tv production has been a sham. they were doing an “investigation” but only investigating anyone that trump thinks might help kavanaugh. the vote is set to be scheduled as soon as possible. the only hope now is to keep up the pressure to call these senators who will decide and hope that one of them will put country over self-interest. @blueravenartist
.
phone numbers of senators in the comments.

text:
we are entering the archetype of the invisible woman.
.
archetypes exist to teach us about a side of ourselves we may not be able to name.
.
who is the invisible woman?
.
she’s the rage and anger that we mask by saying “i’m fine”.
.
she’s the post-partum woman who cries to herself in sorrow and joy while holding her new baby.
.
she’s underground, nourishing all the trees while they appear dormant and dead.
.
she’s the woman who just miscarried and has to show up to work like nothing happened.
.
she’s writing a #metoo status over and over again and can’t share, for many reasons.
.
she is the comfort in our dreams when we’re too afraid of being awake.
.
she’s the one that picks out your tarot cards.
.
she’s the w.o.c that gets left behind and ignored by literally every system she experiences.
.
she’s the blood that heals and cleanses us.
.
she’s the abused, neglected, and overlooked in our world.
.
she’s the bones you are gathering to piece yourself back together.
.
she rises up in order to speak truth and grow from the ashes.
.
the invisible woman is in us all. she’s the force, our shadow, our ability to return to hard things days after day.
.
the invisible woman is what lives in us as we die for the winter.
.
more on my blog. link in profile @rosecandela

text:
[ 10.03.18 ]
happy wacy woman wednesday!!
—
“i do not consider myself courageous or brave; i just got on with it.”
—
mazie hirono is hawaii’s junior united states senator. after practicing law in honolulu, she served in the hawaii house of representatives from 1985-1995. from 1994-2002, she was the lieutenant governor of hawaii. from 2007-2013, she was a member of the us house of representatives. finally, in 2013, she became hawaii’s first female senator. she is also the us’s first asian-american woman senator, first buddhist senator, and the first senator born in japan. she is the longest-serving member of hawaii’s congressional delegation. she has supported gun control and reproductive rights. in 2017, two months after undergoing surgery for stage-four kidney cancer, she flew to d.c. to vote against the repeal of the affordable care act. she is also a member of the senate judiciary committee, which is currently overseeing the supreme court nomination of brett kavanaugh. senator hirono has stood in support of the #metoo movement and dr. christine blasey ford. she has committed to asking every court nominee, under oath, if they have a history of sexual assault or harassment. we are heartened by the hard work and bravery she brings to the u.s. senate!
—
#wacyop #wacywomanwednesday #maziehirono #womeninpolitics #feminism

text:
1/ tonight i skyped with @bad_ass_blindy and she took this screen cap of me messing around to amuse myself. i feel it pretty much sums up my personality. 
2/ i've had a hard week. both of us are prone to #anxiety, i also get bouts of #depression. i'm having to actively avoid the news to stop myself from completely shutting down. i had a really bad day yesterday, slipping back in to some old thought patterns. 
over night i turned a corner though, finally acknowledging what was going on. like a lot of people i feel like parts of my past are being played out on this horrific, unavoidable, grand scale. it's grotesque. that's about all i can really say about it.

this morning i woke up feeling better, so i decided to go to work looking #cute. 
i think i nailed it.
.
.
.
.

text:
i was 21 or 22 when it happened to me. honestly, i might have been 23– i don’t remember. i actually don’t remember how i got there. i suppose i drove, but could have rode with a friend, but i don’t even remember if any of my friends were there. .
.
.
i remember the bedroom and saying no repeatedly. i remember feeling scared and ashamed that i had gotten myself in that situation— i shouldn’t have drank so much. it goes dark from there. i literally remember nothing. i only know something awful happened in that room because of a horrific situation that happened days later (nsfw). .
.
.
i told no one. i was so embarrassed and thought it was my fault. and i don’t actually remember the incident (truly a gift from god.) depression and an eating disorder followed. .
.
.
i went back and forth on whether or not i should share this. i own a small business and am a leader in my local fitness community. is this tmi? will people think differently of me? but then i realized the young girls who benefit from my story far outweigh the folks who i make feel uncomfortable. .
.
.
now i don’t think it was my fault. i remember 100% saying no, so it really doesn’t matter how much i had to drink. if you have a story like this and need someone to talk to, i’m here. dm me, txt me, call me. i’m here for you and so are so many other strong women who have had enough. also, i hope it is a scary time to be a man. it’s about to get a whole lot scarier because we aren’t going anywhere. #metoo

text:
domestic violence is one of the top health concerns in the country. the violence and abuse affect not just the women and men involved but also their children, families, and communities.

understanding its definition and various abuses will help you take action effectively against its many signs of abuse.
💜
💜
💜
💜
💜
💜
#whatsthetea #domesticviolence #anyone #victim #domesticabuse #october #notalone #metoo  #awareness #instawomen #womenempowerment #support #trending #movement
💜 domestic violence 💜
the infliction or threat of acts of violence or abuse against another person living in the same household, especially a family member or intimate partner. 
physical abuse 💜
any type of violent behavior inflicted on the victim which can include hitting, biting, slapping, battering, shoving, punching, pulling hair, burning, cutting, pinching, etc. physical abuse also includes denying someone medical treatment and forcing drug/alcohol use on someone. 
sexual abuse 💜
occurs when the abuser coerces or attempts to coerce the victim into having sexual contact or sexual behavior without the victim's consent. this often takes the form of marital rape, attacking sexual body parts, physical violence that is followed by forcing sex, sexually demeaning the victim, or even telling sexual jokes at the victim's expense.  emotion abuse 💜
involves invalidating or deflating the victim's sense of self-worth and/or self-esteem. emotional abuse often takes the form of constant criticism, name-calling, injuring the victim's relationship with his/her children, or interfering with the victim's abilities. 
economic abuse 💜
takes place when the abuser makes or tries to make the victim financially reliant. economic abusers often seek to maintain total control over financial resources, withhold the victims access to funds, or prohibit the victim from going to school or work. psychological abuse 💜
involves the abuser invoking fear through intimidation; threatening to physically hurt himself/herself, the victim, children, the victim's family or friends, or the pets; destruction of property; injuring the pets; isolating the victim from loved ones; and prohibiting the victim from going to school or work.

text: #metooneveryou that’s what i stand for and please spread the word!  yes it happened to #metoo and yes #timesup and it will change.  i held my grand daughter for the first time and vowed to her #metooneveryou and i know in my heart that we can change this horrible silence and shame about sexual abuse that plagues this society!  we as a nation have to come together in love and be willing to talk about it and heal from it.  of course women are angry, they have every right to be.  everyone has a right to be.  if i was holding my grandson i would be saying the same thing and feel justified in my feelings.  too many people are persecuted or victimized as we call it and left alone in their shame to suffer in silence.  i look at dr ford and i see a hero that changed the course of history. she spoke for all people who have never had the temperament or courage to stand up for fear of retaliation.  when a warrior tells her story of being abused, believe her.  the party was non eventful for everyone else around her, so they will not remember the party, the house or anything 36 years ago.  trauma imprints into a warriors brain forever, the name of the person, the place, though not exact unless it happened frequently in one place. my mission in this life is to create safe places where women and men can finally show up and tell their story.  a place of non judgment and acceptance and love so that the healing process may begin.  this allows the warrior to look at the story and begin to separate the shame from them and place it back on the perpetrator.  this is how forgiveness starts to take place and healing becomes eminent.  if we can’t heal our generation and take responsibility for what happened to us, the cycle will perpetuate itself.  anger fuels the fierce love that will change the world when all is said and done.  my sobriety has blessed me in so many ways these last 27 years.  i have become aware of things i never knew existed, felt pain i never knew i had yet it has all been worth it. #theshamelesswarrior #sobrietyismylove #believeher #attitudeofgratitude #onedayatatime #soberwomen #sobrietyrocks #endabuse #alwaysbelieveabuse

text:
more than ever, i am feeling the weight of motherhood. apart from the day to day exhaustion of raising a toddler, our current political climate has gotten my head in a spin.
🤲🏿
i, like so many women, have been reminded this past week of all the shame, discomfort and sadness that has accrued in my 35-year-lifetime from mistreatment by men.
🤲🏾
from the time of my earliest memory, there have been countless men who have sexually harassed me. friends, employers, colleagues, you name it. for most of my life, i believed sexual harassment was just was something to be expected and that i needed to ignore it, laugh it off, or even worse, take it as a back-handed compliment.
🤲🏽
i have had multiple traumatic dreams of being sexually assaulted but no memory of an attack. where does this imprint come from? maybe my ancestors, maybe the media, or maybe because it’s the terrifying truth and fear of almost all women.
🤲
i used to travel internationally a lot in my former career. one night when i was out celebrating carnival in spain i had had a little too much to drink and didn’t realize that a group of men were following me up a stairwell to the bathroom. luckily, a male friend of mine did and saved me. i was lucky, but am constantly reminded how many are not. one story of many.
🤲🏼
i hear my sisters stories and feel so connected to them by this issue. the reality that 1 in 5 women will raped in their lifetime is why most women have suffered from shame and/or trauma caused by a male.
🤲🏻
all men are not the problem. many are trying to help. our culture is so backwards though and even men being raised by strong women get sucked into the vortex of shaming and sexualizing women’s bodies, many without ever really questioning if it’s right or not because everyone is doing it. as a mother with a son, i feel deeply and urgently that it is my greatest responsibility to raise a man who does not buy into this patriarchal society. a man who will honor, respect and celebrate the incredible power and sacredness of a female and her body. help a momma out if you have any golden tips for this giant task. it’s overwhelming and heavy and it’s really gotten me fired up.

text:
hey! i turned 21 this weekend!!!! 20 was one heck of a year. i travelled to 6 countries by myself, went to yoga school @krantiyoga, became a real live yoga teacher, started @warrior.yoga, met amazing people, including my wonderful @idafarneman (who is coming to canada next week to visit !!!!!) and kept on working on my degree @uottawa. 
i’m so grateful for the way everything has ended up, but it really wasn’t always this way and it would be misleading to make it seem like it has. things, in the past, were dark and hard and scary and painful a lot of the time. i never want anyone to look at this page and see something unattainable because that’s simply untrue, and if you told me 5 years ago that this is what 20 would look like for me i wouldn’t have believed you. 
yet here we are. i’ve put an article on my blog (link in bio) about my past and how i’ve ended up here. i’ll warn you that it’s pretty long. read it, or don’t, but i want you to know that you’re not alone, and wherever you are is a great place to start. yoga can and will take you a long way, if you let it. 
if you want to get involved in yoga but you don’t know how, or you’re unable to afford classes, please let me know. we will work it out. there’s a place for everyone in yoga somewhere, i promise. i promise!!!!! 💙 
#metoo

text:
part 1: this is a topic i’ve debated talking about publicly for a long time, but the events playing out on the national stage over the past couple of weeks have made it clear that there’s power in sharing your story, for both personal catharsis and to contribute your experiences to the larger dialogue.
.
this is the first post in a 3 part series (with totally unrelated photos) because it was much longer than i anticipated and i feel the story is too important to be relegated to the comments.
.
this was extremely difficult to write, and even more difficult to share, but i hope my experience can help you in some way or at least provide a new perspective.
.
tw: four years ago today i testified at a university hearing against the man who sexually assaulted me.
.
i had anxiously been waiting for that day for months after a prolonged investigation because who has time to investigate a sexual assault during summer vacation?
.
but the day had arrived. i had my support system. and i felt strong until all of the fears that had kept me up at night for months began to come to fruition.
.
i had studied the school’s handbook and spoke with the title ix coordinator beforehand so i knew exactly what to expect during the hearing.
.
i was told there would only be 3 members from a larger committee who would be in the room to listen to the testimonies and come up with findings, but when i walked in i found tables arranged in a semicircle with 11 people sitting behind them.
.
worse, despite being contrary to both the school’s policies and federal law, he was also in the room, seated behind a curtain next to the table where i was to sit.
.
i gave my testimony. the committee asked what felt like a million questions (including some about my sexual history). he asked me something (through a proxy), which i remember being completely random and irrelevant. i nearly broke down trying to advocate for myself to have the same rights he was being given. i felt numb.
.
speaking my truth in that room was the most difficult and demoralizing experience of my life.
.
i walked back to the room where my support system was waiting, shaking & sobbing in disbelief, and explained what had just happened.

.

text:
this has been an emotional time for me, like i know it has been for so many. i’ve been channeling that energy into my making and falling in love all over again with #ceramics and @toriamos, and just like that i threw my tallest vessel to date. 
this one is for @amnorris ✨

take care of yourselves lovelies and honor your emotions right now. let them course through you, and i promise you’ll come out stronger on the other side.

text:
this is a picture from may 2016, just before i started the job i am currently on hiatus from. i loved my work as a scientist, it was really important to me, i worked hard for it, and i am really good at it. when i first inquired about the possibility of a permanent job, the head of the project was so excited to have me.  i had been a subcontractor on the project for a year, working from another location. they created a job description just for me - as lead of the human-machine interface design team for a futuristic, highly autonomous aircraft - and brought me into the company “in record time” - as i was told. my job was to develop a type of “virtual copilot“, so i worked closely with pilots, developers, mechanical and flight engineers, as well as serving as the main point of contact for our hmi focused government sponsors. 
i sit down for one of the first conversations with the main pilot on the project - who is the chief pilot for the company - and ask something to the effect of “what type of things do you want to hear from your copilot”? he turns to me and says “the only thing i want to hear from my copilot is “nice landing! and i’ll take the fat one.” the table erupted in laughter. he looks at me and says “oh, sorry”. i’m away from that job because the environment eventually triggered a ptsd episode stemming from childhood sexual trauma.  i should not have had to say that when i asked for someone to be with me in a closed door meeting with a boss that made me uncomfortable. 
sexual harassment in the workplace is real. it’s happening right now. it’s time for a change. we will not be degraded, disregarded or devalued any longer. i’ll be sharing more experiences as an intelligent, passionate, talented, ambitious woman in male dominated industries because the stories need to be told - because we need change. the future is female! 
#feminist #believesurvivors #believewomen #respectwomen #femininerising #fuckthepatriarchy #whyineedfeminism #valuewomen #metoo #weallcamefromawoman #thefutureisfemale #womeninaviation #womeninengineering #supportwomen

text: i haven’t publicly spoken much about what’s happening with kavanaugh - and i realized it’s because i’m just not surprised. men disregarding the words & bodies of women, feeling entitled, and throwing fits is literally the fabric of the patriarchy. we as women have been conditioned to stay unstable and unfocused. we have been conditioned to distract ourselves with trying to achieve patriarchal standards of beauty, to compete with other women, to believe our place is the 𝐨𝐧𝐞 𝐦𝐞𝐧 𝐬𝐞𝐭 𝐟𝐨𝐫 𝐮𝐬. we have been conditioned to be quiet - because when we speak we are faced with an entire government of men who discredit and demean us, at best - and at worst...well, we all know what that looks like. we live in a constant state of fear, even if we are not consciously aware of it, because the number one cause of death to women is...men. men, on the other hand, are conditioned to feel and behave as if they are entitled to everything they want, including the space and physical bodies of women. right here, i feel the (socialized) need to give a caveat about “not all men” but you know what? those of you who don’t feel you fall into these categories and yet do nothing to dismantle the patriarchy are just as dangerous as those men who perpetuate crimes against women. your silence is and will always be a win for the oppressors. i am extremely privileged because i was raised by a (innately but unbeknownst to him, bless his cotton socks) feminist father and a european and progressive mother. i also spent my entire education learning about feminism (how many of you checked out when you read that word? interesting, huh?), gender, socialization, politics, and the politicizing of bodies. i have been immersed in understanding the horrors of what the patriarchy actually means, a reality that many of you seem to just be understanding for the first time - even if you have been the victim of it in the most traumatizing and direct ways. i am also privileged because i am a lesbian, and have never been, nor ever will be, for the pleasure of men. i do not have to go into the lion’s den, smelling of blood and hoping for the best. caption continued in comments 👉🏼
name: Ivy Les Vixens

text:
nina pirrotti is a former nyc prosecutor and a civil rights lawyer who has co-counseled with gloria allred and nathan goldberg on a number of cases, including the 2012 litigation against uconn on behalf of five students and alumnae who are survivors of sexual assault. she has spoken nationally on topics involving sexual harassment and assault on campuses and in the workplace. she will be speaking again on this subject at the national employment lawyers association’s harnessing the power of the hashtag #metoo movement conference in mid-october 2018 and at the aba’s employment rights and responsibilities conference in march 2019. attorney pirrotti has published articles on a wide variety of civil rights topics, including workplace investigations involving sexual harassment allegations.
#garrisonlevinepstein #civilrights #uconn #students #survivors #sexualassault #harassment #workplace #employment #employeerights law #biglaw #rights #justice

text:
“to the extent that #metoo and time’sup destigmatize things that have historically been considered private matters and not the kind of thing you talk about, there’s now a potential to catalyze more sustained efforts to address the important issues.” – suzanne kim
•
suzanne kim is focused on family—not her own, specifically, but family as it’s viewed through the lens of the law. as a legal scholar, she’s turned her own lens in the direction of the ways in which family, gender, sexuality, race, ethnicity, and culture intersect. kim wants to know how, for instance, the legal understanding of family privacy can be a detriment to gaining redress for domestic violence, and how a parent’s sexuality or sexual orientation can affect family matters like child custody in cases of divorce.
•
“my scholarship focuses, in part,” she says, “on the role that the legal regulation of family plays in reflecting and creating social inequality.”
•
like her scholarship, her influence runs deep and wide. as a professor at @rutgers.law in newark, she teaches courses in family law, civil procedure, and sex discrimination, she is a member of the executive committee of the association of american law schools section on family and juvenile law and the section on law and the humanities. kim is also the founder and director of the rutgers center for gender, sexuality, law, and policy and a member of the executive committee of the institute for research on women at rutgers—to name just a few examples of her commitment in the real world to the principles she studies in academia.
•
click the link in our profile to read more about suzanne kim and her work, as well as other stories on #rutgers today, your source for the latest #rutgers news. #rutgerspride #rutgersexcellence

text:
rp @lightmoveme ✨lokah samastah sukhino bhavantu- -
✨“may all beings everywhere be happy and free, and may the thoughts, words, and actions of my own life contribute in some way to that happiness and to that freedom for all.”
-
✨by chanting this mantra, we move from our personal self and radiate a prayer of love for the world around us. it takes us from the egoic, little self, and its limited world view, and radiates from us global wellbeing. it is a reminder we are a part of the universe and can positively impact all of creation.
-
✨we are all one
inherent in the mantra is that we are all beings sharing the same planet and we must care equally for other inhabitants. we are interconnected to all, the illusions of separation dissolve.
-
✨”may all beings be happy and free” elevates our awareness to more conscious thought. we do not wish only for ourselves, but recognize we are part of a collective effort on this planet. if i wish myself these blessings, so too may i wish them on all others. this honoring of divinity within you calls onto this planet what we need. do unto others as you would have them do unto you.
-
✨compassion
recognizing we are all one, we can move into sincerer compassion for ourselves and those around us. -
✨we cannot achieve true happiness if we cause unhappiness to other living beings, nor we can be free if we deprive others of their freedom. #respectlife #loveanimals #letthembe #theirlivesmatter #lovethemall #animallovers #animalkingdom #familyiseverything #savetheocean #savetheearth #peaceandlove #govegan #crueltyfree #environment #environmentalist #planetearth #metoo #wildlife #wildlife_perfection #animalshaverights #proteina #babyanimals #donttakeourplanetforgranted

text:
sat nam beautiful one,
.
it’s been a wild year for the collective healing of the feminine, yes?
.
for me, i’ve learned so much from other women speaking out, rising up and no longer giving a sh*t about behaving from “shoulds”.
.
even though i’ve been through one of the hardest times of my life this year, i’ve learned to fully open myself to me again. laughter like never before is coming. thank you kali for showing me the gift on the other side of destruction.
.
🦋
.
two years ago i started running an online course for women who were interested in reclaiming their power and bringing wholeness back into their lives..
.
recently, the universe has pushed me (honestly against my own preference) to offer this course again. and i’ve listened.
.
so here’s the deal: we gather virtually once a week for 40’days and go deep together in guided meditation and shamanic practices.
.
you receive one kundalini yoga and meditation class video weekly during his time to heal, nourish and replenish yourself.
.
you have the experience of a 1:1 intuitive healing session with me where you may receive anything from channeled guidance to practical resources for your physical health.
.
you will receive the gift of a personal kundalini meditation to support you on your healing.
.
40 days to support your own unique healing constellation. and as we all know, when we heal the individual we also heal the collective.
.
we begin october 25th. link in bio.
.
that’s it.
.
i love you, thanks for being you.
.

text:
why i didn't report in the #metoo era
.
dr. strange sat across from me, shaking his head regrettably.
.
"i want you to remember this, m, because some day it might be very important.  if you ever feel unsafe or threatened, never let a patient get between you and the door. ... you're an easy target."
.
"what does that even mean?", i remember thinking to myself.
.
8 years later, i understand exactly what that means.
.

text: dear friends: instead of sharing my #metoo feels from the last few weeks, i've decided to post that time i walked up 72 steps and felt like a champion. you might know that i'm a big fan of the #rocky franchise. i watched the movies with my mom when i was a kid and they shaped my childhood (take from that what you will). so this morning before a day of meetings, i made my first trip to the philly art museum and "ran" up the rocky steps while listening to gonna fly now. sometimes you need to do something silly to get out of a funk. thanks @officialslystallone for a lifetime of memories.

i have known robbie since i was 12yrs old, he was roommates with me and my bf at the time when i was in my late teens, he did my chest tattoo when i was about 21-22 when i worked at the tattoo shop with him, he raped me when i was 27yrs old, 2yrs ago on october 23rd. i went to hang out with someone i thought was a friend, someone i thought i could trust, to drink and talk about a mutual friend that i was missing and having issues with. i got too drunk and i though i would be safe at his house because he had never shown me otherwise. until the next day when i woke up to him naked and on top of me without my permission. i was asleep he took away any chance i had to say "no". i was vulnerable in so many ways and he took advantage of that in such a disgusting and damaging way. please don't let this happen to other women, i'm begging you, he is a manipulative liar and he hasn't changed, please don't let him hurt anyone else, please

tweet_full: #metoo

text:
in the last week, so many women have been feeling raw and angered over conversations in the national news about sexual assault. and of course, it is only one of many times of conversation since the #metoo movement sprang to life. ⠀
.⠀
in 2016, activist tarana burke started using the phrase #metoo in her work with women of color who have endured sexual assault. in 2017, the actress alyssa milano began asking people to use burke's phrase as a hashtag to share their stories. since then, there have been thousands and thousands of stories on social media with that hashtag. ⠀
.⠀
the show #mymetoo, curated by artistic director of vashon center for the arts, will open here on friday. the show contains art created by pacific northwest artists, inspired by these conversations. (this triptych — ladies in waiting — was created by heidi stair.) we hope you can come in to see it. ⠀
.⠀
have you been able to share your story? have you ever taken great pain and created something for other people? what is the role of art in all this? we would love to know your thoughts.⠀
.⠀
.⠀
.⠀
#metoo #metoomovement #artfrompain #vashoncenterforthearts

text:
my name is christopher cantrell. at the age of 20, i was raped. for three years i did everything my mind and body could do to erase, manipulate, or ignore this memory.  not only had i refused to report my assailant, but i had refused to accept my own trauma.
at 23, i began seeking counseling and therapy to cope with my symptoms of ptsd, depression, and anxiety. i ran from my demons for three years before i lost the stamina to avoid it. for three years i tried to pretend my life was normal like some of my friends; that my world was not the shattered glass i continued to walk through. 
therapy helped. confiding in loved ones created a safe space. slowly pieces came back together. some are still their sharp and jagged edges, but with careful hands and softer love, i’ve been putting together the pieces of a tattered and stained past. 
christine blasey ford carried her burden for 36 years. she continued to fight and strive for a life that defied her abuser. she is an icon, a heroine, and the reason i choose to speak out now. without her courage and bravery i would not be typing this. even as i write these words, my heart burns to delete all of this-to stay hidden and quiet was once a way to placate the terror. but no more. 
i stand with dr. ford and countless others. the one in four women who have experienced this tragedy. the one in seventy-one other men who have also faced this nightmare. 
now we stand together. locked arms and hearts. i believe in dr. ford, i believe in myself, i believe in you. you are loved, you are worthy, and you are what the world needs to hear. shaking hands and shaking voice, you are here to stand tall like she did in front of this committee and in front of this president who dares to mock her truth. it is our time to be brave.
today, i am 26. today the past still haunts me in the form of night terrors and politics. i am still learning to accept myself, my past, and love. i am still learning to love myself, day by day, and what bravery truly means. 
today and onward, i push myself to practice what i’ve learned.
#ibelieveher #metoo #personal #youareloved #lovetrumpshate

text:
i had plans to share other things today.⠀
⠀
but yesterday i saw the horrible reports of what trump’s mockery of #drchristineblaseyford. his heaping of humiliation from the world’s widest platform onto a woman who has lived with the effects of a traumatic sexual assault for nearly my entire lifetime.⠀
⠀
i don’t expect better of trump. he’s a narcissistic, crude, frail ego possessing , lying, and misogynistic demagogue. there’s no doubt in my mind that he was humiliated by the nyt report of his entire brand being a fraud—which wasn’t even new information—so he lashed out. ⠀
⠀
i’m disgusted by him, but barely have the energy left for anger at him. power corrupts & he’s rotten.⠀
⠀
but the crowd. the arena full of people laughing. loving every second of feeling empowered at the expense of a sexual assault survivor who courageously opened her most raw anguish up to the world that it might prevent a man from obtaining power one with his character should never have.⠀
⠀
i am angry. angry as fuck. ⠀
⠀
i know life is hard. i know these are humans every bit as much as i am. i know that the actual evil genius of the white men who possess the grossly concentrated wealth & power of this nation is buying the gop & fueling said party’s base with fear of “other” that makes it palatable to place the blame on society’s most vulnerable populations.⠀
⠀
that said, there is no excuse for ever being so desperate to feel like you are #winning that you actively harm not just innocent people but oppressed & suffering people.⠀
⠀
i refuse to operate out fear that these ugly tactics will erase all the beauty & good until we devolve into civil war. i choose love, to believe that just as i could go from evangelical to free, nearly 100% gop voting for 2 decades to early adopter of the likes of @ocasio2018 & @betoorourke, these people can also wake up.⠀

but as i do the work on me & to help others i will still be real damn angry. no one should be treated this way.⠀
⠀
and #trumpets, you can laugh at my “liberal tears.” but #theyoungpeoplewillwin & those of us with a conscience will #crushthepatriarchy & #crushwhitesupremacy.

tweet_full:
i had plans to share other things today.⠀
⠀
but yesterday i saw the horrible reports of what trump’s mockery of #drchristineblaseyford. his heaping of humiliation from the world’s widest platform onto a woman who has lived with the effects of a traumatic sexual assault for nearly my entire lifetime.⠀
⠀
i don’t expect better of trump. he’s a narcissistic, crude, frail ego possessing , lying, and misogynistic demagogue. there’s no doubt in my mind that he was humiliated by the nyt report of his entire brand being a fraud—which wasn’t even new information—so he lashed out. ⠀
⠀
i’m disgusted by him, but barely have the energy left for anger at him. power corrupts & he’s rotten.⠀
⠀
but the crowd. the arena full of people laughing. loving every second of feeling empowered at the expense of a sexual assault survivor who courageously opened her most raw anguish up to the world that it might prevent a man from obtaining power one with his character should never have.⠀
⠀
i am angry. angry as fuck. ⠀
⠀
i know life is hard. i know these are humans every bit as much as i am. i know that the actual evil genius of the white men who possess the grossly concentrated wealth & power of this nation is buying the gop & fueling said party’s base with fear of “other” that makes it palatable to place the blame on society’s most vulnerable populations.⠀
⠀
that said, there is no excuse for ever being so desperate to feel like you are #winning that you actively harm not just innocent people but oppressed & suffering people.⠀

text:
black moon lillith in astrology
this aspect of the moon's elliptical is a very important and powerful energy at play now within our collective. she represents hidden and taboo aspects of the feminine archetype. the repression of her natural power appears as deeply threatening or disturbing. she has come into our awareness now to help us integrate and reclaim her. "lilith represents something that has become unconscious and is striving to become conscious again. let's call it archaic energy, spiritual femininity, something akin to the wisdom of the goddess. as long as we don't have access to this energy we experience it psychologically as loss, suppression, isolation, emptiness, addiction and above all power struggles*
bml is currently in aquarius at 6 transiting brett kavanugh's natal venus conjunct lillith.  kavanugh's sun, mercury, venus, lilith and ceres are all being affected by transiting lillith and mars.....his chart is fascinating as it plays out with potus and the u.s. chart -the themes of change and abuses of power. 
you can find your natal lillith on astro.com. this is the place you experience her primal power and where you may reclaim a suppressed aspect of the divine feminine.
* hannelore traugott

this. be brave, my friends. your voice has power. use it to help, not harm. 💚

every time trump (or anyone else) mocks sexual assault victims - all we hear is “i wouldn’t believe you either.” this is why women don’t report sexual assault. 1 in 3 women experience sexual assault, harassment, or rape in their lifetime. i am one of them. you know me, and you definitely know many more of these women. they are my friends, family, colleagues, classmates, clients...and they are yours too. and, yet, you cheer when trump mocks dr. ford and vote for him after he publicly brags about assaulting women. this is why women haven’t trusted you with their stories. 
to white women, who voted overwhelmingly for trump - i beg you to please get curious about why you don’t support and believe women, your sisters. and why you support these men who lie to/about us, bully us, mock us, and assault us. think about the messages your support sends to future generations, young girls and boys. they are listening. we need you, we are stronger together. 👭
#metoo #timesup #ibelieveher #neverthelessshepersisted #whyididntreport #womenempowerment #womensupportingwomen #sisterhood #whitewomen #downwiththepatriarchy #allmen #lovetrumpshate #strongertogether

text:
as i ran on the csu campus this morning i was reminded of all the sunrises i experienced during my time at @iowastateu with @cyclonetrackxc. i haven’t been able to really articulate all the pain that has been presenting itself since the terrible passing of #celiabarquín, also a cyclone athlete. as a woman, i should be able to be physically active without the fear that i will be stalked, attacked, or even killed. since her death, i now run in fear, and i hate that. my heart aches for her friends and family and the cyclone community. i want injustice of individuals to end. in gender, ethnicity, race, religion, i want to run free, without fear. 
#cyclones #iowastateuniversity #iowastateathletics #isu #csu #metoo #enoughisenough #morningrun #runlikeagirl

text: jaimi ~ working so intimately with women, i know how deep and common the shame, pain, and powerlessness felt from sexual victimization is. the #metoo movement has brought a lot of relief and healing, we've been able to connect and unite in our painful stories as well as take a huge burden of shame off. we can see our repression and abuse as a whole now which is huge. but it’s far from enough, we're still so far as last week showed us. i want to use our collective horror and rage at seeing the pervasive sexual violence and society’s current protection of it to fuel change. i support @rainn, an amazing organization that provides support services to rape, abuse, and incest survivors as well as provides public education about sexual violence and advocates to improve public policy. i also think we need to show our men and boys a different way and @acalltomen does great work to show them how to embrace a healthy, respectful manhood that doesn’t include violence and discrimination. i'm hopeful that out of this pain there will be beautiful change and progress. ⚡️ @jaimibrooks ⚡️ jaimi wears @rachelpally with hair by @thedrybar make-up by @kerrycrawford photographed by @anniemcelwain at @festoon_la ⚡️ #midlandgalsforchange

text:
these are indeed very scary times for men. here are some useful tips to avoid being a victim of false sexual assault accusations: 
1.  if you go to a party, either have only one drink, or only drink soda or water, so you can keep your wits about you. never get tipsy around people you don't know and trust fully—it could come back to haunt you later. even around people you fully trust, remember that most false rape allegations come from people you know. be vigilant!
2.  use the buddy system, so you always have a witness! only go to the bathroom with a friend, or ideally with a group of friends. always have a friend walk you to your car, in case you run into a strange woman in the parking garage. never go camping or hiking or biking or running or even just walking alone. never go to a bar or concert or party or event alone; that is just asking for it.
3.  if you're going out anywhere, make sure you text the specifics of your plans to at least one or two trusted friends, in case they need to verify your whereabouts to police later. you may also consider using a location sharing app so you have proof of where you were and when.
4.  if you're going to exercise, make sure that you bring a friend, or even better, just exercise at home. never go through a park alone. there might be a woman there who could accuse you.
5.  when you're heading to class or work, never listen to music or podcasts on headphones. you need to listen carefully to your surroundings to make sure no woman is accusing you of anything.
6.  when you're getting into your car at the end of the day, always check your backseat to make sure there aren't any women hiding back there. never take shortcuts through alleys or parking lots that aren't extremely well lit, in case a woman is hiding there, waiting to accuse you.
7.  only take out the trash, walk the dog, get your mail, go to the atm, or get gas during daylight hours. most false rape accusations happen at night, and you don't want to become a statistic. if you must go out alone at night, make sure to get your phone out... more at https://mobile.twitter.com/daniellemuscato/status/1046807809122340865

text:
the brett kavanaugh case.🤨 ”the #metoo movement has seen women come forward to speak of their experiences of sexual assault and sparked a wider conversation about sexism in society and how men treat women.

within this context, many see the case as a litmus test to gauge if society has changed - and whether women will be believed when they speak out.

but others say the case is an example of one person's word against another - and if it costs mr kavanaugh a place on the supreme court then it will set a dangerous precedent”

this case is another example of women being encouraged to come forward about  their experiences of sexual assault and when they finally do , ‘men’ like donald trump almost practically applaud the accused man. 
is he guilty? and should a man being accused of several counts of sexually assaulting women be allowed a seat on the supreme court? the outcome is yet to be decided . #brettkavanaugh

text:
#خودت_باش_دختر
از باور کردن دروغ‌هایی که درباره‌تان گفته می‌شود دست بردارید تا تبدیل به همان کسی شوید که واقعا هستید. 
نوشتهٔ #ریچل_هالیس 
ترجمهٔ هدیه جامعی 
از پرفروش‌ترین های آمازون و نیویورک‌تایمز در سال ۲۰۱۸ 
دخترها از سراسر دنیا از من می‌پرسن که چطور... چطور وقتی زمین می‌خورم دوباره بلند ‌شم؟ چطور توی زندگی‌م تغییر ایجاد ‌کنم؟ چطور با این ضربۀ روحی کنار بیام؟ چطور دوباره شروع کنم؟ چطور این بچه ها رو بزرگ کنم؟ سؤال‌هایی از این دست که از نظر من همه یک جواب دارند. 
بعضی از شماها حتماً از این یادداشت‌ها از من گرفتید... می‌گفتم که «تو یک مبارزی. خیلی قوی هستی. تو هر کاری که بخوای می‌تونی انجام بدی.» اما بعد از مدتی متوجه شدم اون جوابی که می‌خواستم رو نمی‌گفتم. اون‌وقت بود که سعی کردم کتابی بنویسم که جواب تمام سؤال‌های شما توش باشه، اگه دوست من بودید یا اگر خودم بودید؛ توی سن بیست، بیست‌وپنج، یا سی سالگی. 
و جواب اینه: تو قدرت تغییر زندگی‌ت رو داری. دیگه دنبال پاسخ سؤالاتت توی اینترنت نگرد. تو جواب رو می‌دونی. تو ابزارش رو داری. 
فکر کردم اگه این کتاب رو بنویسم و همۀ کشمکش‌های زندگی خودم رو توش بیارم، یا زمان‌هایی که نمی‌دونستم چه‌کار کنم و گیج بودم، وقت‌هایی که زمین خوردم، اشتباه ‌کردم؛ و اگه مسیری که خودم رفتم رو نشونتون بدم، اون‌وقت جرئتی بهتون می‌دم که توی مسیر خودتون هدفمند قدم بردارید. من نخواستم نظاره‌گر غرق شدن شما باشم. من توی محبت کردن آدم خشکی هستم، پس هرکس که مشکلش رو پیش من مطرح کنه باید پیه همه‌چیز رو به تنش مالیده باشه. می‌دونید، «من هم همین‌طور (#metoo)» از قدرتمندترین کلمات زبان انگلیسی هستند. و من از این تفکر یک بستر ساختم. و همچنین از این باور که «من اول شروع می‌کنم.» من دستم رو بالا می‌گیرم و راجع به افسردگی بعد از زایمانم حرف می‌زنم؛ راجع ‌به مصرف بیش از اندازۀ الکل، گرفتاری‌های ازدواجم، دشواری‌های بچه بزرگ‌کردنم، شرمساری از بدنم، سوءاستفاده و اهمال‌کاری و آسیب‌های دوران کودکی‌م. من دستم رو بالا می‌گیرم و اولین کسی می‌شم که بهتون می‌گه همۀ این اتفاق‌ها براش افتاده. و نه‌تنها این اتفاق‌ها رو تجربه کردم، بلکه تونستم با موفقیت ازشون گذر کنم. امیدوارم این کتاب جسارت انجام این کار رو به شما بده. امیدوارم وقتی داستان‌هام رو می‌شنوید و این کتاب رو می‌خونید بفهمید که تنها نیستید. پس به‌همین‌دلیل این کتاب رو نوشتم.

انجام بدی . » اما بعد از مدتی متوجه شدم اون جوابی که می‌خواستم رو نمی‌گفتم . اون‌وقت بود که سعی کردم کتابی بنویسم که جواب تمام سؤال‌های شما توش باشه، اگه دوست من بودید یا اگر خودم بودید؛ توی سن بیست، بیست‌وپنج، یا سی سالگی . و جواب اینه : تو قدرت تغییر زندگی‌ت رو داری . دیگه دنبال پاسخ سؤالاتت توی اینترنت نگرد . تو جواب رو می‌دونی . تو ابزارش رو داری . فکر کردم اگه این کتاب رو بنویسم و همۀ کشمکش‌های زندگی خودم رو توش بیارم، یا زمان‌هایی که نمی‌دونستم چه‌کار کنم و گیج بودم، وقت‌هایی که زمین خوردم، اشتباه ‌کردم؛ و اگه مسیری که خودم رفتم رو نشونتون بدم، اون‌وقت جرئتی بهتون می‌دم که توی مسیر خودتون هدفمند قدم بردارید . من نخواستم نظاره‌گر غرق شدن شما باشم . من توی محبت کردن آدم خشکی هستم، پس هرکس که مشکلش رو پیش من مطرح کنه باید پیه همه‌چیز رو به تنش مالیده باشه . می‌دونید، « من هم همین‌طور ( از قدرتمندترین کلمات زبان انگلیسی هستند . و من از این تفکر یک بستر ساختم . و همچنین از این باور که « من اول شروع می‌کنم . » من دستم رو بالا می‌گیرم و راجع به افسردگی بعد از زایمانم حرف می‌زنم؛ راجع ‌به مصرف بیش از اندازۀ الکل، گرفتاری‌های ازدواجم، دشواری‌های بچه بزرگ‌کردنم، شرمساری از بدنم، سوءاستفاده و اهمال‌کاری و آسیب‌های دوران کودکی‌م . من دستم رو بالا می‌گیرم و اولین کسی می‌شم که بهتون می‌گه همۀ این اتفاق‌ها براش افتاده . و نه‌تنها این اتفاق‌ها رو تجربه کردم، بلکه تونستم با موفقیت ازشون گذر کنم . امیدوارم این کتاب جسارت انجام این کار رو به شما بده . امیدوارم وقتی داستان‌هام رو می‌شنوید و این کتاب رو می‌خونید بفهمید که تنها نیستید . پس به‌همین‌دلیل این کتاب رو نوشتم .

text:
i felt super-conspicuous on my way to last friday's #stopkavanaugh protest. i stood with my giant protest sign in a quiet capitol hill neighborhood coffee shop, waiting to see if anyone else could make it. at 11:30, i decided to trust my gut, gave myself a pep talk in the bathroom, and headed out solo.

walking towards the supreme court, i didn't exactly know where to go or what to expect. at the back of the building, i heard a bullhorn and chanting in the distance. so, i walked through a side courtyard towards the sound, and ran into a stream of people and signs flowing towards the front steps of the court. as the protestors continued to arrive, i realized that i had merged with the front of the group and now i was standing behind the podium, accidentally at the very center of the protest.

senators and celebrities swarmed in with their staff, preparing to rally the crowd. leaders from @womensmarch and @humanrightscampaign huddled near me going over details for the speeches about to start. the energy around me was incredible to witness.

on the podium, i watched a constant rotation of activists, assault victims, politicians, and local leaders sharing powerful stories and calls to action. joan baez, standing in front of me, got up to lead us in singing a famous civil rights song together (see video). behind the podium, i observed the flow of the people making this all happen. coordinating speeches, keeping an eye on what was unfolding politically in real time, strategizing about what to do after the speeches ended.

the last two years, i've felt paralyzed. frustrated by dc representation. feeling unqualified to do anything. preoccupied with unpacking my own personal shit first, like #whiteprivilege + #metoo. anxiously feeling like the only person in my social circle called to direct action. not knowing where to start.

it changed me to be there friday, to cry with strangers while we listened to survivors' stories. to be surrounded by people who care enough to show up and try to make a fucking difference somehow. we don't all have to march, but we all have to do our part.

next: what happened at the senate building that afternoon.

text:
***new blog post***
.

this morning i published the most difficult post i've ever written on the blog.  i've been sitting on these words for four years; occasionally they would come back to me, and for whatever reason, the timing wasn't right or i lacked the courage, and now today, the timing is right.  i've been pumping myself up throughout the day with my daughter's favorite song by rachel platten - .
.
“this is my fight song
take back my life song
prove i'm alright song
my powers turned on
starting right now i'll be strong
i'll play my fight song
and i don't really care
if nobody else believes
cause i've still got
a lot of fight left in me" .
.

which seems appropriate seeing the words i wrote are for my daughters and your daughters and for the future generations of daughters. .
.

here it is. in all honesty, i don't feel very brave but as i've learned,
.
. . "courage is not the absence of fear. it is moving forward in spite of the fear." .
.

just keep livin.
(full link in bio)

text: it makes sense that bullies use shame as their primary tool.  alienation and separation can weaken a person or at least diminish their confidence and sense of self worth.  recovery allows me to reserve shame for only those moments in which i have made a poor or harmful choice.  not an unpopular choice.  but a poor choice.  it is life changing and life giving to be free from feeling the shame others may attempt to impose.  healthy boundaries make it easier to recognize when the shame i feel is legitimate or actually just grief over being treated unkindly. someone else being an asshole, no longer causes me shame.  only me, being an asshole can do that. thank you @brenebrown for teaching us about shame resilience. 💥

text:
the objectification theory as proposed by barbara fredrickson and tomi-ann roberts states that the objectification of a woman or a girl can eventually lead to an increased feeling of anxiety or self-awareness. the woman supposedly immediately internalizes the status that the society has given to her and sees this outcome as a primary view of herself.

fredrickson and roberts argue that in some way, the objectification of women can even affect the mental health of the female.the perspective of the public imposed on the female body can lead to body monitoring and obsessive eating patterns which will eventually lead into an internal feeling of shame or anxiety. fredrickson and roberts argue that influences from the new wave feminists and scholars have put the female body in a sociocultural perspective. this has led to a new dimension of the perspective of the body, however, it has also underemphasized the significance of viewing the female body in a biological as well as a sociocultural perspective. they argue that the one should not be overshadowed by the other, as it is the combined effect that has created a social construction behind the body image.

text:
i am sadly not surprised at all to see right wing #evangelical #christians defending #trump's mockery of #christineblasleyford and supporting #kavanaugh no matter what the #fbiinvestigation brings. i grew up hearing horror stories of #women whose #pastors told them to stay with their #abusive husbands and "stand strong" for his salvation, submitting as the #bible says to do. there were some stories my grandmother, my pastor, would hear of women who never made it out alive of those relationships. the false teaching and twisting of scripture in order to put a yoke of bondage around the necks of women and keep #patriarchal control of society is a disgrace and even blasphemous. #jesus gave equal rights, equal witness and empowerment to women, and the entire new testament confirms this, yet they cherry-pick 2 verses in which paul is addressing one particular #church and a specific issue/problem within that church. they even misquote the verse and twist the original meaning. paul also told men to submit themselves to women to the point of being willing to die for them. and he sat under women teachers. but the actual words of the bible and spirit/values of christ do not matter to those whose political agenda and legalistic, #pharisee-ical approach to religion is their god. i want #drford and all survivors to know i speak for the entire #christiandemocrats of america and #whatwouldjesuspod team when i say we are standing with you, praying for you, and when trump mocks assault #survivors, and women in general, and those such as #sarahsanders excuse it, i believe the spirit of god is very grieved.
i will just add that our latest podcast was a deep dive into this topic with an evangelical self-proclaimed "#feminist" pastor (also my dad) and we explore the topic broadly, if you wish to check that out here: http://www.christiandemocratsofamerica.org/blog/2018/09/27/what-would-jesus-pod-episode-16-kavanaugh-republicans-and-women/.
end of rant. #christiansresist #wwjd #metoo #christianfeminist #believesurvivors

"i am over the passivity of good men. where the hell are you? you live with us, father us, befriend us, love us, brother us, get nurtured and mothered by us, so why aren't you standing with us? why aren't you driven to the point of madness and action by the rape and humiliation of us?”-eve ensler.

sitting back quietly during the last few weeks was difficult. as i watched dr. christine blasey ford and brett kavanaugh’s testimonies and read articles written from povs of both sides of the aisle, i swallowed a lot of words and held on too tightly to some emotions. i share my story again to inspire strength in survivors (i’m always here if you need a safe space) and action in allies. link is in my bio.

text:
so, who here has a negative reaction to the word diet?
🙋🏻‍♀️.
me too.
🤦‍♀️.
after 25+ years of dieting, feeling like i was getting nowhere in terms of managing my weight and feeling good about me i was ready to take the concept of dieting & throw it out the window, light it on fire & do a dance to celebrate.
🔥.
okay, maybe not the dancing - that might have been extreme  but the rest? hell yeah! and i know i am not alone. the struggle is real.
💥.
i saw a post yesterday by a fitness trainer who had one simple message. that a diet is simply what we eat. it’s not negative, it’s not evil - it’s just what we eat.
🌯.
so being real with you friends, he is 💯 right. maybe we are attaching too much emotional baggage, blame, anger & more than the word diet deserves.
💥.
mindset is everything. if we attach a slew of negative emotions to the concept of losing weight & getting healthy, how committed are we going to be to it? not very, i bet. but if we focus on being positive about the process, the lifestyle, how we feel vs how we look, trying new and delicious foods ... then the process becomes something positive, fun and a lifestyle we can enjoy long term.
✨.
we have the power friends. isn’t it time we started making getting healthy a wonderful one?
🙌.
.
.
.
.
.
#myfabulousfitlife #diet #dieting #healthylifestyle #healthy #healthandwellness #healthcoach #wednesdaywisdom #wednesday #instastory #metoo

text:
when i first started this project, i had a lot on my mind: what if people don’t like it? what if i’ll lose a lot of followers?  isn’t it better to stay neutral on controversial topics like this?⁣
⁣
but then i realize, if i don’t put this into the world, then i’m letting the dark side win. you’ve probably heard this quote: “the world suffers a lot. not because of the violence of bad people, but because of the silence of good people.”⁣
⁣
and i don’t want to be that good person who decides to be a bystander. it’s time to rise up and fight for the survivors. 50% of the profits will be donated to rainn, the nation’s largest anti-violence charity. let’s do this ♥️ tap on the pic or click the link in my bio to shop 💪🏻

text: i  feel great pain. psychological pain, which i can not describe in words. it freaked me out from the inside. the feeling of non-existence strikes me. apparently, we should always read the book before we judge it. apparently life is unique. for me, the world has become a cold place. i am sitting in a room and i think that my life will not improve anymore. my whole family is guilty. not only those who started it, but also everyone who saw and did nothing. everyone wanted to avoid responsibility. i was at the point where i kept the tablets in my hands and told myself the last goodbye. the moment i took it, i started to regret it very much. i was more sad than ever. i wanted, i want to live very much. i can not make it anymore. the pain in my heart does not end. the words that he finds are not comparable. this is probably the end. lost tears. lost years and months. #ptsd #deppression #mentalhealth #therapy #helpme #metoo #abuse #psychology #mentalillness #fight #survivor

text:
i, melanie joyce johnson, am currently walking myself out of financial abuse. as a christian woman, you wouldn’t notice the abuse because the scars don’t show. you wouldn’t notice unless i told you.
💜
this may not be serena’s story, but it’s mine and the story of many others.
💜
it’s the destruction of credit, credibility, identity, loss of trust, shame, disempowerment, and the struggle and pain of re-establishing yourself financially so that you can get back to a sense of normalcy.
💜
i’m thankful that @allstatepurplepurse and @serenawilliams are exposing this again this year. there is joy in taking the steps to help yourself get 🔙🔛🔝🔜. if you or someone you know is facing financial abuse, please know that there are places that offer free legal services and financial assistance. dm me for more info and i can help you begin to identify those places.
💜

text:
titolo: gli incredibili 2
regista: brad bird
data d'uscita: 2018
casa di produzione: @pixar e walt disney pictures
cast: c. t. nelson, h. hunter, s. vowell, h. milner, e. fucile, s. l. jackson, c. keener, b. odenkirk, b. bird e j. banks

dopo quasi quindici anni dall'uscita nelle sale de 'gli incredibili', ritorna sul grande schermo la famiglia di supereroi più amata del cinema. 
in pieno clima #metoo, il regista brad bird, dona il ruolo di superoe principale ad una donna, elastigirl, e stravolge l'ideale di 'famiglia tradizionale', ponendo il gentil sesso come 'capo famiglia' e dando all'uomo il compito di occuparsi degli affari domestici: questo è uno degli aspetti più belli ed interessanti dell'opera. importante è anche la critica ai media, che, con forza, chiarisce che, chiunque abbia il controllo di questi, può soggiogare ogni persona, infatti il villain di questo film, l'ipnotizzaschermi, adopererà proprio la televisione per controllare la terra.
'gli incredibili 2' oltre ad uno script divertente e avventuroso, che nonostante qualche difetto, riesce a mantenere viva per tutto il film l'attenzione dello spettatote, è tecnicamente fantastico, con disegni ben fatti e con una scenografia più cupa del precedente episodio, che mostra a pieno la disillusione riguardo la società odierna del regista: l'unico super potere che può combattere l'odio e rivoluzionare questo mondo è l'unione famigliare.

nonostante 'gli incredibili 2' non sia alla pari del primo film, è un prodotto assolutamente godibile, simpatico, a tratti toccante ed adatto a tutte le età.

text: @regran_ed from @avivaromm -  as a midwife, much of my life centered naturally on women, wombs, and babies. and continues to as a women’s md. we learn so little about our wombs - so many women have no idea, for example, what their cervix is, how cervical and vaginal mucus change throughout the month, what’s normal bleeding and what’s not, and for so many, our womb’s become a battlefield and zone of pain and scars - severe period pain, endometriosis (not actually in the womb but we associate it with our womb because it’s womb-like tissue cause the pain and scarring), heavy bleeding with cycles, between cycles, trauma from abuse, pregnancies that wouldn’t happen miscarriages that did, labors that don’t start or don’t go the way we hope leading to cesarean and scars, and the hysterectomies that almost 50% of women will eventually have. i wonder, what does you womb mean to you? whether or not ‘she’s’ still in your body. what suffering, joy, creativity, loss, pain, does this part of your body hold or mean to you? i’ve been so blessed to have a joyous relationship with my own - but at 52, my cycles are changing and i celebrate my new life phase and mourn maiden and mother as i enter ‘crone’ - or what i love to call ‘wisdom years. by sharing our womb stories we can heal so much for ourselves and each other. (deep thx to the artist who created this womb - if anyone knows plz lmk so i can credit. #periodpain #miscarriage #hysterectomy #endometriosis #womb #midwifery #midwife #metoo - #regrann
name: Lené • Lené's Birth Services
tweet_full: @regran_ed from @avivaromm -  as a midwife, much of my life centered naturally on women, wombs, and babies. and continues to as a women’s md. we learn so little about our wombs - so many women have no idea, for example, what their cervix is, how cervical and vaginal mucus change throughout the month, what’s normal bleeding and what’s not, and for so many, our womb’s become a battlefield and zone of pain and scars - severe period pain, endometriosis (not actually in the womb but we associate it with our womb because it’s womb-like tissue cause the pain and scarring), heavy bleeding with cycles, between cycles, trauma from abuse, pregcies that wouldn’t happen miscarriages that did, labors that don’t start or don’t go the way we hope leading to cesarean and scars, and the hysterectomies that almost 50% of women will eventually have. i wonder, what does you womb mean to you? whether or not ‘she’s’ still in your body. what suffering, joy, creativity, loss, pain, does this part of your body hold or mean to you? i’ve been so blessed to have a joyous relationship with my own - but at 52, my cycles are changing and i celebrate my new life phase and mourn maiden and mother as i enter ‘crone’ - or what i love to call ‘wisdom years. by sharing our womb stories we can heal so much for ourselves and each other. (deep thx to the artist who created this womb - if anyone knows plz lmk so i can credit. #periodpain #miscarriage #hysterectomy #endometriosis #womb #midwifery #midwife #metoo - #regrann

anita hill// thank you.  27 years ago... you lead this fight we are still embroiled in... you weren’t protected enough then but you fought with dignity anyway.  you answered the call placed before you.  we— i’m talking #blackwomen— are often the #pioneers for everything.  we have to be. the intersections of our gender and race renders us often overlooked, undervalued and left alone to speak for ourselves and our children.  i always say if we can solve the issues that plague black women, this country would truly be the best place on earth.  it astonishes me how #brave #strong and #consistent we are generation after generation.  often history will tell you it was only the black men and white women who lead movements of humanity and equality. but we’ve been here, always have been.  you were there 27 years ago... fighting for us!  you sitting there at #clarencethomas confirmation hearings, you had everything to lose... but you made a crack that day, that will eventually break the dam... thank you for being patient with the rest of us to speak up and say #metoo! text:
sometimes, i have to take a moment to feel inspired to write something for my captions on instagram. lots of subjects are on my mind every day but now i know what i need to address. this time it is about the women who have been scared to bring forward their traumatic life event and now finally have found the right amount of strength to do so. it is sickening that we live in a society where women get ridiculed or taunted for speaking up about the abuse/rape/mistreatment they had to endure. 
thank you @rainbowlovekiki for sharing your story. it broke my heart reading about your traumatic experience. i am very inspired by your strength and honesty.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
to all the women out there who have been put through hell, know that i believe you and i want to support you. ❤️
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
together, we are stronger.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
👚 @no.cruelty
🎥 @devanvalentine @ross.burwell thank you for the great video! 💕🙏🏼
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
#compassion #ibelieveyou #metoomovement #metoo #feminism #nocruelty

text:
i feel things moving. shaking up. loosening heart strings. change. i’ll admit, it hasn’t been pleasant; it’s been a deep inner battle, but because of this, i’ve had some new revelations. some of them i really don’t like, but they’re all opening doorways to something deep within. •
this is a crazy time we are all living through and it truly has not come at a more prominent time in my own life. i’ve been carrying a lot of burdens that i have not been able to deal with yet, and this has brought everything right in front of my face...it’s scary and tough. i can’t push it away any longer. its affected my relationship with my husband and loved ones. it’s affected my relationship with myself...for too long.
•
but i’m counting this as my opportunity: to dig myself out of the grave and be reborn, transformed. i won’t give up. i won’t let what happened to me stop me from becoming who i am meant to be. 
for those of you who are dealing with imbedded sexual assault trauma coming back to life from the recent kavanaugh situation, i hope you know that we are stronger together. i am here for you with open arms and to listen to your story. we can get through this together and rise up from the depths. you are worthy. you are deserving to thrive in this life and not just get by, day by day. •
you are loved. you are love.

text:
dile no al abuso infantil🚫
.
📰📲💻📺📟 en los últimas semanas he visto muchas noticias sobre de una creciente ola de abuso sexual en niños y adolescentes, que parece ser una epidemia, lo triste, es que el abuso en todos los casos notificados se ha perpetuado por un conocido. es evidente la falta de educación sexual en los hogares. proteger nuestros niños es un deber de todos!

1. conoce los hechos y la realidad. estar informado sobre el abuso sexual infantil, ayuda a proteger a los niños.

2. debes saber con quién dejas el niño y qué hacen.la mayoría de los casos de abuso sexual infantil suceden cuando un menor está a solas con un adulto.

3. habla abiertamente del asunto con tu hijo. la comunicación construirá la confianza. debe ser su lema 'mi cuerpo es mi territorio y nadie lo toca sin mi permiso'.
.
4. aprende a detectar e identificar los indicadores del abuso sexual. ya sean físicos, emocionales o de comportamiento.

5. no reacciones con exageración a un posible caso de abuso. ¡denúncialo!. infórmate, sepa reaccionar. sepa adónde ir, a quién llamar y cómo reaccionar. el abuso sexual es un delito, sin importar quien lo proporcione.

6. actúa siempre, aunque solo tengas sospechas y no pruebas. confía en tu intuición y ten el valor de denunciar o poner en conocimiento a un servicio de protección al menor.

7.  involúcrate. se voluntario de apoyo a las organizaciones que luchan contra el maltrato y el abuso sexual a menores. usa tu voz y tu voto para convertir tu comunidad en un lugar más seguro para los niños.
.
🔊rompe el silencio. la prevención depende de eso.
.
📣di no más! 📣
